        ALTHOUGH_NOT_BEING_AS_FINANCIALLY_STABLE_AS_MY                                = 10364,  -- Although, not being as...financially stable as my interviewees, I'm forced to act like some ne'er-do-well and participate from the fringe. Act being the operative word here.
        LUCKILY_MY_CONSTANT_EFFORTS_HAVE_BEEN_HANDSOMELY_REWARDED                     = 10365,  -- Luckily, my constant efforts have been handsomely rewarded with the juiciest tidbit I've plucked in a while.
        IT_WENT_A_LITTLE_SOMETHING_LIKE_THIS_WE                                       = 10366,  -- It went a little something like this: We want you to collect intelligence pertaining to the formation of contemporary Adoulin. Now, this is a highly classified mission, so we can't have people eavesd--
        AHEM_YOU_GET_THE_IDEA_ANYWAY_THE_REWARD                                       = 10367,  -- <Ahem> You get the idea. Anyway, the reward's an astounding # bayld! This might be the first scoop I've uncovered without having to embellish anything! I'd look like a shame to the profession if I passed on this job. Look like being the operative phrase here.
        THEN_AT_THIS_MOST_IMPORTANT_OF_TIMES_YOU                                      = 10368,  -- Then, at this most important of times, you emerge from the mists of anonymity and appear before me. Is this serendipity? Fate? Nay...
        NECESSITY                                                                     = 10369,  -- Necessity!
        THE_GODDESS_SMILED_UPON_ME_AND_SENT_THIS                                      = 10370,  -- The Goddess smiled upon me and sent this % to bear witness to the history we'd forge together!
        TO_SUMMARIZE_THE_WHO_WHAT_WHERE_WHEN_WHY                                      = 10371,  -- To summarize the who, what, where, when, why, and how of it all...
        I_INVEST_YOU_WITH_THE_POWER_TO_CARRY                                          = 10372,  -- I invest you with the power to carry out this most meaningful of assignments!
        I_SAID_THAT_YOU_GET_TO_CARRY_OUT                                              = 10373,  -- ...I said that you get to carry out this mission!
        HOW_S_THAT_SOUND_LIKE_THE_STORY_OF                                            = 10374,  -- How's that sound? Like the story of a lifetime?
        WELL_DOES_IT_OF_COURSE_OF_COURSE_NOT                                          = 10375,  -- Well, does it? Of course! Of course not! I dunno... Could you repeat that?
        MY_JOURNALIST_S_INSTINCTS_TOLD_ME_THIS_WOULDN                                 = 10376,  -- My journalist's instincts told me this wouldn't go as planned. As planned being the operative phrase here.
        HAVE_YOU_REALIZED_THE_SCALE_OF_THIS_ASSIGNMENT                                = 10377,  -- Have you realized the scale of this assignment yet? Have I finally awakened your journalist's instincts?
        UGH_I_KNEW_THIS_WOULDN_T_GO_AS                                                = 10378,  -- Ugh, I knew this wouldn't go as...wait, you'll do it!?
        OKAY_THEN_TIME_TO_DELEGATE_DUTIES_YOU_LL                                      = 10379,  -- Okay, then. Time to delegate duties. You'll gather the necessary details and I'll write the story. It'll be a three-legged race to the finish line!
        TO_REVIEW_I_NEED_STUFF_PERTAINING_TO_THE                                      = 10380,  -- To review, I need stuff pertaining to the formation of Adoulin as the Sacred City, so...there should be some facts lying in wait around Adoulin.
        MAYBE_THE_YAHSE_HUNTING_GROUNDS_AND_CEIZAK_BATTLEGROUNDS                      = 10381,  -- Maybe the Yahse Hunting Grounds and Ceizak Battlegrounds hide some important clues, too...? I don't know, I'm just grasping at chocobo feathers here.
        I_LL_TAKE_WHATEVER_YOU_FIND_AND_CRAFT                                         = 10382,  -- I'll take whatever you find and craft from it the most eye-catching piece this continent has ever read! Eye-catching being the operative word here.
        NOW_GET_CRACKING_THIS_INFORMATION_ISN_T_GOING                                 = 10383,  -- Now, get cracking! This information isn't going to dig itself up.
        SO_WHAT_MARVELS_HAVE_YOU_BROUGHT_ME                                           = 10384,  -- So, what marvels have you brought me?
        HMMM                                                                          = 10385,  -- Hmmm...
        THIS_MIGHT_MAKE_FOR_A_MILDLY_ENTERTAINING_READ                                = 10386,  -- This might make for a mildly entertaining read, but nothing eye-catching. I'll need some more information.
        WITH_MY_AUTHORIAL_PROWESS_WE_JUST_MIGHT_BE                                    = 10387,  -- With my authorial prowess, we just might be able to make something of these. Let's get started!
        FIRST_WHAT_ABOUT_THIS_IT_LOOKS_IMPORTANT_DOESN                                = 10388,  -- First, what about this %? It looks important, doesn't it?
        DOES_IT_LOOK_IMPORTANT_OH_IT_DOES_NOT                                         = 10389,  -- Does it look important? Oh, it does. Not particularly.
        ALRIGHT_THEN_NEXT_UP_IS                                                       = 10390,  -- Alright then, next up is...
        THIS_THING_I_GUESS_IT_S_THIS_LOOKS                                            = 10391,  -- This thing! I guess it's %. This looks important, too, right?
        PHEW_I_M_GLAD_THAT_S_FINISHED_NOW                                             = 10392,  -- Phew, I'm glad that's finished. Now be prepared to have your mind melt in amazement of my summarization skills!
        WHAT_A_DISCOVERY_WE_VE_DETERMINED_THAT_NOTHING                                = 10393,  -- What a discovery! We've determined that nothing important ever happened in the history of Ulbuka. Case closed.
        WHAT_RE_YOU_THINKING_IF_THAT_S_ALL                                            = 10394,  -- What're you thinking!? If that's all we have to report, our client's going to annihilate us in a fit of rage! Annihilate being the operative word here! Let me read through these anyway and you try to pick out what sounds important.
        TWO_HUNDRED_YEARS_AGO_ALL_ACTIVITY_RELATED_TO                                 = 10395,  -- Two hundred years ago, all activity related to the colonization of the continent was suspended indefinitely. The populace retreated behind Jorius Yett and the city shifted its economic focus to mercantilism.
        ADOULIN_S_GLORY_HAD_COMPLETELY_VANISHED_ONE_HUNDRED                           = 10396,  -- Adoulin's glory had completely vanished one hundred years after the suspension of pioneer activity. Coffers now depleted from the continued support of a system that was eventually banned, the city's military might was insufficient to assert influence over even the tiniest of nations.
        TAKING_THESE_ISSUES_TO_HEART_A_MAJORITY_OF                                    = 10397,  -- Taking these issues to heart, a majority of the Twelve Orders came forth and proposed the abolition of imperial rule. The royal family capitulated to their request and abdicated in favor of a council composed of leaders from the orders.
        IT_SUPPOSEDLY_TOOK_MUCH_LONGER_THAN_EXPECTED_TO                               = 10398,  -- It supposedly took much longer than expected to establish safe and reliable trade routes due to the intensity of the currents in Ulbuka's surrounding seas. The owner of this chart was also apparently bound for the Tavnazian Marquisate.
        THE_MOTHER_OF_ADOULIN_MAESTER_SVENJA_S_COUNTENANCE                            = 10399,  -- The mother of Adoulin, Maester Svenja's countenance is without imperfection. Her kind gaze emanates warmth and light that embraces all in loving affection.
        FOLLOWING_THE_KING_S_ABDICATION_A_BODY_POLITIC                                = 10400,  -- Following the king's abdication, a body politic formed from leaders of the Twelve Orders was established and the Sacred City of Adoulin was born.
        THAT_SHOULD_DO_IT_I_THINK_HOW_ABOUT                                           = 10401,  -- That should do it, I think. How about you? There anything that'll nab us heretofore unfathomable riches? Heretofore unfathomable being the operative phrase here.
        ANYTHING_OF_VALUE_I_THINK_SO_NOT_AT                                           = 10402,  -- Anything of value? I think so. Not at all.
        ALRIGHT_THEN_LET_ME_SEND_THIS_OFF_VIA                                         = 10403,  -- Alright, then let me send this off via the Couriers' Coalition. Now all we have to do is find out the identity of our client...
        BUT_WHO_CARES_WHO_HE_IS_AS_LONG                                               = 10404,  -- But who cares who he is, as long as we get paid!
        AS_FOR_YOUR_SHARE_OF_THE_BAYLD_TAKE                                           = 10405,  -- As for your share of the bayld...take this for now. The rest should come in a day or so.
        NEVER_ONCE_IN_ALL_MY_YEARS_DID_I                                              = 10406,  -- Never once in all my years did I bother to investigate the history behind this continent, but it turns out there are actually some events that pique my interest. Some being the operative word here.
        BUT_MY_POCKETS_ARE_OVERFLOWING_WITH_BAYLD_SOME                                = 10407,  -- But my pockets are overflowing with bayld! Some seems to fall out with each step I take. This is definitely a problem I could get used to.
        YEAH_YEAH_YEAH_I_KNOW_YOU_LIKE_TO                                             = 10408,  -- Yeah, yeah, yeah. I know you like to think you contributed to the report as well. About that...
        AFTER_PAYING_OFF_ALL_THE_DEBTS_I_OWED                                         = 10409,  -- After paying off all the debts I owed around town, I only have so much left. This is all that's physically possible for me to part with. Physically possible being the operative phrase here.
        I_LL_GET_YOU_THE_REST_EVENTUALLY_I                                            = 10410,  -- I'll get you the rest eventually, I swear! You know I'm good for it.
        BUT_MY_EMOTIONS_HAVE_DRIED_UP_EVEN_FASTER                                     = 10411,  -- But my emotions have dried up even faster. I've not a drop of sympathy left to spare for people who don't go by the name Roskin.
        ACK_UM_ABOUT_YOUR_PORTION_OF_THE_REWARD                                       = 10412,  -- Ack! Um, about your portion of the reward...I kind of lost it in one of the games held by the Mummers' Coalition.
        THE_REWARD_ALSO_TURNED_OUT_TO_BE_MUCH                                         = 10413,  -- The reward also turned out to be much smaller than we expected, so...that's how the trail cookie crumbles.
        OKAY_OKAY_OKAY_WHY_DON_T_I_DRAW                                               = 10414,  -- ...Okay, okay, okay! Why don't I draw on my infinite stores of largesse and give you half the bayld I have on hand out of the kindness of my heart? Largesse being the operative word here.
        MY_GRANDFATHER_S_GRANDFATHER_HAD_A_PIONEERING_SPIRIT                          = 10415,  -- My grandfather's grandfather had a pioneering spirit at least the match of any of the pioneering heroes of old. His career, however, was ill-fated...
        YOU_SEE_ALL_ACTIVITIES_RELATED_TO_COLONIZATION_WERE                           = 10416,  -- You see, all activities related to colonization were banned at the time. His devotion knew no bounds, though, so he went into the jungle all by himself despite his family's pleas to put down the pickaxe.
        IF_MEMORY_SERVES_ME_HE_HEADED_FOR_THE                                         = 10417,  -- If memory serves me, he headed for...the Ceizak Battlegrounds. Sadly, no one ever heard from him again after he left.
        OUR_FAMILY_HAS_BEEN_OPPOSED_TO_COLONIZATION_EVER                              = 10418,  -- Our family has been opposed to colonization ever since. For me, I just don't want anyone to experience the terrible pain my ancestors did.
        ALL_THE_YOUNG_UNS_THESE_DAYS_ARE_WETTING                                      = 10419,  -- All the young'uns these days are wetting themselves at the mere mention of pioneering... <Sigh> I really must be getting too old.
        YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_THE_FORMATION_OF                                       = 10420,  -- You want to know about the formation of Adoulin? Ummm...sorry, but I don't really know anything about it. I bet the Scouts' Coalition would, though.
        WHOA_THAT_S_SOME_ANCIENT_STUFF_YOU_RE                                         = 10421,  -- Whoa, that's some ancient stuff you're trying to dredge up, there. The various coalitions around here would be much more knowledgeable about that kind of stuff than me.
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_INFORMATION_ABOUT_THE                                   = 10422,  -- If you're looking for information about the old pioneering days, that guy recruiting for the Pioneers' Coalition probably knows a lot more than me...
        THE_SEAS_HAVE_BEEN_QUITE_ROUGH_AS_OF                                          = 10423,  -- The seas have been quite rough as of late. I cannot imagine anyone making their way to the Yahse Hunting Grounds via ship without the help of a map to delineate the currents.
        OF_COURSE_OUR_WHITE_CAP_HARDENED_CAPTAIN_IS                                   = 10424,  -- Of course, our white cap-hardened captain is more knowledgeable about these waters than everyone on the continent. Do not forget to thank him for his lifesaving expertise should you seek passage on his vessel.
        OH_MAESTER_SVENJA_HOW_I_YEARN_TO_BE                                           = 10425,  -- Oh, Maester Svenja, how I yearn to be swept up in your toned-yet-lithe arms and lose myself in your deep, calming gaze...
        OH_TH_THE_SCOUTS_COALITION_S_SINCE_WE                                         = 10426,  -- Oh, th-the Scouts' Coalition...? S-since we're experts at stealth, we can do wh-whatever we want wh-wherever we want! In dark alleys, in other p-people's homes...bweheheh!
        OH_PARDON_ME_YOU_RE_SEARCHING_FOR_RECORDS                                     = 10427,  -- Oh, pardon me. You're searching for records on Adoulin's founding?
        I_BELIEVE_YOUR_BEST_BET_WOULD_BE_TO                                           = 10428,  -- I believe your best bet would be to flip through some of our historical primers.
        THEY_RE_ALL_ON_THAT_SHELF_OVER_THERE                                          = 10429,  -- They're all on that shelf over there. You can have one, but we kindly ask you to refrain from taking any more with you.
        ALL_THE_DOCUMENTS_WE_VE_COMPILED_IN_THE                                       = 10430,  -- All the documents we've compiled in the coalition are for public use. Search 'til your fingers are covered in paper cuts if you want.
        COMPENDIUMS_RELATING_TO_ADOULIN_S_MYRIAD_HISTORICAL_EVENTS                    = 10431,  -- Compendiums relating to Adoulin's myriad historical events line the shelf.
        DAILY_REPORTS_FROM_COALITION_MEMBERS_ARE_SCATTERED_CARELESSLY                 = 10432,  -- Daily reports from coalition members are scattered carelessly about, yet are written in a surprisingly refined hand.
        ID_5EV_BV_HE7                                                                 = 10433,  -- %%5EV bv%-\hE7
        IT_KEEPS_US_DRY_GOING_FROM_EAST_TO                                            = 10434,  -- It keeps us dry going from east to west,t We know that, among walkways, it's the best,t Iiit's Biiig Briiidge!t
        NOW_THE_TIMES_HAVE_CHANGED_T_AND_SO                                           = 10435,  -- Now the times have changed,t And so have you.t Let's not leave Big Bridge behind.t Let's build it anew!t
        I_VE_HEARD_ALL_ABOUT_THE_GOSSIP_PEOPLE                                        = 10436,  -- I've heard all about the gossip. People are saying the curse of the founder king is true and that the colonization effort is doomed!
        EVEN_YGNAS_S_ADOULIN_HAS_DISAPPEARED_FROM_SIGHT                               = 10437,  -- Even Ygnas S. Adoulin has disappeared from sight, and he's the one who advocated pioneering in the first place! This does not bode well...
        EASTERN_ADOULIN_IS_CHOCKABLOCK_FULL_OF_ARROGANT_NOBLES                        = 10438,  -- Eastern Adoulin is chockablock full of arrogant nobles and their inflated senses of self-worth. Be careful when approaching them, for even the most trivial perceived slight will set them off on a tirade belittling your woeful lack of civility.
        THEY_RE_ALSO_THE_REASON_THE_PEACEKEEPERS_COALITION                            = 10439,  -- They're also the reason the Peacekeepers' Coalition was erected here. They act as if pedigree equals privilege and want someone to protect their historic structures of cultural import from us filthy vermin at all times.
        WE_THE_PEACEKEEPERS_COALITION_ARE_HERE_TO_SERVE                               = 10440,  -- We, the Peacekeepers' Coalition, are here to serve and protect the citizens of Adoulin! Outsiders like you wouldn't know the first thing about how to keep Adoulin safe from...well...the outside!
        THIS_FINE_EDIFICE_HOUSES_WHAT_S_KNOWN_AS                                      = 10441,  -- This fine edifice houses what's known as the Peacekeepers' Coalition. I'll let your imagination run wild trying to figure out what our particular group does.
        I_KNOW_YOU_RE_FROM_THE_MIDDLE_LANDS                                           = 10442,  -- I know you're from the Middle Lands, but don't go being all buddy-buddy with the Pioneers' Coalition. The tangled webs they weave have ensnared many.
        WELCOME_TO_LE_CAF_I_DES_LARMES_I                                              = 10443,  -- Welcome to Le Caf%i des Larmes. I cannot say that I enjoy gazing upon the vellication of your muscleless physique, but as the heir to this fine establishment, I will not refuse you service.
        I_CANNOT_SAY_I_ENJOY_THE_GROTESQUE_NATURE                                     = 10444,  -- I cannot say I enjoy the grotesque nature of your deformed countenance, but as the heir to this fine establishment, I will not refuse you service.
        TAKE_A_LOOK_AT_ALL_THE_FOOD_WE                                                = 10445,  -- Take a look at all the food we have to offer. It can only be found here in Adoulin!
        GRRR_STARE_HE_S_SHE_S_NOT_A                                                   = 10446,  -- Grrr...<stare>... (He's/She's] not a merrrchant...)
        HM_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_THEN_SCURRY_ON                                        = 10447,  -- Hm? You're an adventurer? Then scurry on over to the Pioneers' Coalition before I grab you by the scrrruff and carry you to Western Adoulin myself!
        OHO_A_SOJOURNER_COME_TO_EXPERIENCE_THE_WONDERS                                = 10448,  -- Oho, a sojourner come to experience the wonders of our fine city, are you? Eastern Adoulin surpasses even your wildest expectations for this mysterious continent, does it not?
        I_CAN_SAY_WITH_CERTAINTY_THAT_OUR_SIDE                                        = 10449,  -- I can say with certainty that our side of the city is vastly more dignified than the plebian slum... That is where the Pioneers' Coalition resides, however, so you'll have to brave the filth if you wish to register for the colonization effort.
        THIS_S_MAWGWET_S_HOUSE_SHE_S_THE                                              = 10450,  -- This's Mawgwet's house. She's the maestah of the Scouts' Cowawition.
        IT_DOESN_T_WOOK_WIKE_SHE_WANTS_YOU                                            = 10451,  -- It doesn't wook wike she wants you heeah, so go away. Only I can be her appwentice!
        IT_TAKES_A_CERTAIN_TYPE_OF_GENIUS_TO                                          = 10452,  -- It takes a certain type of genius to sketch a jungle landscape.
        THAT_S_WHY_I_MUST_FOCUS_ALL_MY                                                = 10453,  -- That's why I must focus all my creative energy into a dense ball of concentration. I need my muse to descend from the heavens and set my spirit on fire with a volcanic eruption of inspiration!
        HOW_DOES_A_TRANQUIL_MOMENT_SPENT_AMIDST_THE                                   = 10454,  -- How does a tranquil moment spent amidst the soothing chirps of small birds and the rhythmic crash of waves upon the shoreline sound? This caf%i can provide you with all that and more, my good sir/my fair lady].
        MAINLAND_ADOULIN_NOT_ONLY_HAS_SHEER_CLIFFS_THAT                               = 10455,  -- Mainland Adoulin not only has sheer cliffs that rise high above the ocean, but the city itself is nestled quietly behind Jorius Yett--that enormous gate to the west.
        THIS_VERITABLE_FORTRESS_OF_NATURE_IS_FURTHER_PROTECTED                        = 10456,  -- This veritable fortress of nature is further protected by Western Adoulin, which--fortunately for us--would take the brunt of any attacks that might actually penetrate the city.
        THAT_MEANS_MANY_UNIQUE_BUILDINGS_FROM_ANTIQUITY_HAVE                          = 10457,  -- That means many unique buildings from antiquity have survived to this day. Should you have some spare time, I recommend taking a stroll and getting a good look for yourself.
        STROLL_NORTHWARDS_AND_YOU_SHALL_MEET_WITH_A                                   = 10458,  -- Stroll northwards and you shall meet with a wharf that docks ferries bound for the Yahse Hunting Grounds.
        HAHAHA_YOUR_CONCERN_ABOUT_SEA_MONSTERS_WREAKING_HAVOC                         = 10459,  -- Hahaha, your concern about sea monsters wreaking havoc on Adoulin is certainly a logical one to have. I myself consider the Peacekeepers no more than jesters dressed in steel rather than motley.
        YET_PRAISE_BE_TO_ALTANA_SUCH_A_DREADFUL                                       = 10460,  -- Yet, praise be to Altana, such a dreadful event has yet to occur.
        YOU_RE_ON_THE_HUNT_FOR_A_FLESHLESS                                            = 10461,  -- You're on the hunt for a fleshless sort of prrrey? Well, our ears, eyes, and noses are the best in the reconnaissance business! That's why we're the Scouts' Coalition.
        HMMM_MY_SOURCES_TELL_ME_THAT_THE_INFORRRMATION                                = 10462,  -- Hmmm... My sources tell me that the inforrrmation you seek can be obtained at the Pioneers' Coalition in Western Adoulin.
        WHAT_S_MORE_IMPORRRTANT_THAN_GIL_OR_BAYLD                                     = 10463,  -- What's more imporrrtant than gil or bayld? Information! Looking for some facts to sink your teeth into or grab your arrrchnemesis by the throat with? Then step inside the Scouts' Coalition!
        THIS_ABODE_IS_WHERE_GRATZIGG_THE_PEACEKEEPERS_COALITION                       = 10464,  -- This abode is where Gratzigg, the Peacekeepers' Coalition maester, sleeps his nights away when he's not slaving over his desk.
        GRATZIGG_THOROUGHLY_LOATHES_PIONEERS_WITH_HIS_HEART_AND                       = 10465,  -- Gratzigg thoroughly loathes pioneers with his heart and soul. Rumors have it that he even sprinkles his breakfast with flakes of skin from the remains of pioneers he's cornered in alleyways.
        THERE_S_A_LARGE_SYSTEM_OF_TUNNELS_UNDER                                       = 10466,  -- There's a large system of tunnels under this city called the Rala Waterways.
        ALMOST_EVERYONE_WHO_S_BEEN_DOWN_THERE_TALKS                                   = 10467,  -- Almost everyone who's been down there talks about hearing grotesque howls deep within. Some have even seen monsters, they say. Maybe they slip through secret holes to get around the magic barrier...I don't know.
        I_M_YSADEL_A_MEMBER_OF_THE_ORDER                                              = 10468,  -- I'm Ysadel, a member of the Order of Adoulin. My charge is to provide assistance to pioneers in any way possible.
        MY_APOLOGIES_BUT_I_M_AFRAID_I_CAN                                             = 10469,  -- My apologies, but I'm afraid I can't help you if you aren't a pioneer. It's some council decision, so it all goes over my head.
        I_CAN_HOWEVER_POINT_YOU_IN_THE_DIRECTION                                      = 10470,  -- I can, however, point you in the direction of the Pioneers' Coalition. Just cross Big Bridge into Western Adoulin and you can't miss it. They should be able to provide the preliminary aid you require.
        HAVE_YOU_HAD_THE_CHANCE_TO_VENTURE_DOWN                                       = 10471,  -- Have you had the chance to venture down into the Rala Waterways?
        ONE_OF_MY_ACQUAINTANCES_WORKS_IN_THE_CIVIC                                    = 10472,  -- One of my acquaintances works in the Civic Arboretum there. Should you ever tire of culling the monstrosities that lurk down there, please say hi for me.
        YOU_RE_ABOUT_TO_BOARD_A_FERRY_BOUND                                           = 10473,  -- You're about to board a ferry bound for the Yahse Hunting Grounds. This ain't some noble's backyard, though. Many a good man has died right off the boat there, so make sure you're prepared before you board.
        SET_SAIL_FOR_THE_YAHSE_HUNTING_GROUNDS_AYE                                    = 10474,  -- Set sail for the Yahse Hunting Grounds? Aye aye, Cap'n! Let me test the waters more.
        A_WHARF_BE_LYING_BEYOND_HERE_BUT_THE                                          = 10475,  -- A wharf be lying beyond here, but the vessel ain't quite ready yet. Amazing what one sea monster can do to a ship that size, I swear. It'll probably be fit to sail once you register with the Pioneers' Coalition, though.
        PREPARE_YOURSELF_YOUR_FAMILY_AND_EVEN_YOUR_IMAGINARY                          = 10476,  -- Prepare yourself, your family, and even your imaginary companions for life in the jungle with our latest wares!
        GET_LOST_COMMONER                                                             = 10477,  -- Get lost, commoner.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_SILVER_KNIFE                                                   = 10478,  -- ...Welcome to the Silver Knife.
        ONCE_YOU_PROVE_YOURSELF_WORTHY_OF_PRIVILEGED_TREATMENT                        = 10479,  -- Once you prove yourself worthy of privileged treatment, then we will treat you with privilege. Until then, scram.
        YOU_MAY_ENTER                                                                 = 10480,  -- ...You may enter.
        ENTER_THE_PREMISES_OF_COURSE_IT_S_MY                                          = 10481,  -- Enter the premises? Of course, it's my right. No, it's not worth my attention.
        LEAVE_THE_PREMISES_INDEED_I_SHALL_I_STILL                                     = 10482,  -- Leave the premises? Indeed I shall. I still have business here.
        THE_CELENNIA_MEMORIAL_LIBRARY_CONTAINS_RELICS_OF_KNOWLEDGE                    = 10483,  -- The Celennia Memorial Library contains relics of knowledge from ages past as well as the latest-watest illuminated publications. We can't grantaru access to unproven philistines, however. Sorry.
        THE_CELENNIA_MEMORIAL_LIBRARY_CONTAINS_RELICS_OF_KNOWLEDGE_2                  = 10484,  -- The Celennia Memorial Library contains relics of knowledge from ages past as well as the latest-watest illuminated publications. Would you care to enter this vastaru vault of knowledge?
        ENTER_THE_LIBRARY_YES_NO                                                      = 10485,  -- Enter the library? Yes. No.
        THERE_SHALL_BE_NO_STOWING_AWAY_WHILE_I                                        = 10486,  -- There shall be no stowing away while I'm on watch! Only registered pioneers are allowed aboard this vessel, you imposter!
        THE_VESSEL_THAT_DOCKS_BEYOND_HERE_TRANSPORTS_PIONEERS                         = 10487,  -- The vessel that docks beyond here transports pioneers and laymen alike to their very own island plot containing various amenities.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_NOTHING                                        = 10488,  -- What do you want to know about? Nothing. Send me to my Mog Garden! Visiting others' Mog Gardens. Rent-a-Rooms. Mog Gardens. Mog Garden expansion.
        I_M_SURE_YOU_CAN_RECALL_THE_RENT                                              = 10489,  -- I'm sure you can recall the Rent-a-Room you used back in the Middle Lands.
        THE_ONES_HERE_FUNCTION_IN_THE_EXACT_SAME                                      = 10490,  -- The ones here function in the exact same manner as the ones you've already grown to love as your homes-away-from-home.
        IN_ADDITION_TO_RENT_A_ROOMS_WE_ARE                                            = 10491,  -- In addition to Rent-a-Rooms, we are also working to provide pioneers with Mog Gardens.
        I_HATE_TO_BURST_YOUR_PROVERBIAL_BUBBLE_BUT                                    = 10492,  -- I hate to burst your proverbial bubble, but we have yet to receive permission from the council to open them to the pioneering public.
        MOG_GARDENS_ARE_SPECIAL_AREAS_LOCATED_ON_THE                                  = 10493,  -- Mog Gardens are special areas located on the islands dotting the Adoulin Archipelago which have a variety of facilities suited for all your gathering needs.
        ABSOLUTELY_NO_FEE_IS_REQUIRED_TO_TAKE_ADVANTAGE                               = 10494,  -- Absolutely no fee is required to take advantage of this service.
        WE_HOPE_THAT_YOU_UTILIZE_YOUR_MOG_GARDEN                                      = 10495,  -- We hope that you utilize your Mog Garden to the fullest.
        YOUR_MOG_GARDEN_IS_NOW_MORE_LUXURIOUS_THAN                                    = 10496,  -- Your Mog Garden is now more luxurious than ever, thanks to the edification of the Pioneers' Coalition!
        IF_YOUR_GARDEN_S_SERVICES_CAN_EXPAND_THEY                                     = 10497,  -- If your garden's services can expand, they can decrease, right? Not so! You never have to worry about losing what's already part of your Mog Garden, even if the Pioneers' Coalition should fall on hard times!
        YOU_CAN_VISIT_THE_MOG_GARDENS_OF_THE                                          = 10498,  -- You can visit the Mog Gardens of the following party members. Is there anyone's in particular you want to visit?
        VISIT_WHOSE_MOG_GARDEN_NO_ONE_S_S                                             = 10499,  -- Visit whose Mog Garden? No one's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's.
        OKAY_THEN_RIGHT_THIS_WAY_PLEASE                                               = 10500,  -- Okay, then. Right this way, please.
        SORRY_BUT_NONE_OF_YOUR_PARTY_MEMBERS_HAVE                                     = 10501,  -- Sorry, but none of your party members have their Mog Gardens open to anyone at this time.
        YOU_ARE_CURRENTLY_UNABLE_TO_VISIT_THAT_PERSON                                 = 10502,  -- You are currently unable to visit that person's Mog Garden.
        LISTENLISTENLISTEN_I_SAW_A_BLACK_BEASTIE_HOPPING_FROM                         = 10503,  -- Listenlistenlisten! I saw a black beastie hopping from roof to roof!
        I_WANNA_CATCH_IT_AND_TALK_TO_IT                                               = 10504,  -- I wanna catch it and talk to it! Do you think monsters can talk? What would they say if they could? Do you think they even like Humes?
        YOU_RE_DAMN_RIGHT_THIS_ESTATE_BELONGS_TO                                      = 10505,  -- You're damn right this estate belongs to an important person! Just look, it's purrrched upon a hill that overlooks Eastern Adoulin!
        THIS_GRRRAND_ABODE_IS_ACTUALLY_THE_HOME_OF                                    = 10506,  -- This grrrand abode is actually the home of Ikhi Askamot, our minister of education. She's famous not only for her political role, but also because many claim she's the rrreincarnation of legendary geomancer Sih Renaye.
        MOST_OF_ADOULIN_S_WELL_TO_DO_PURCHASE                                         = 10507,  -- Most of Adoulin's well-to-do purchase residences on the top of this hill.
        I_ASSUME_IT_S_SO_THEY_CAN_ACTUALIZE                                           = 10508,  -- I assume it's so they can actualize the metaphor of looking down on the peasantry, but maybe some just do it for the view. There have to be at least a few magnanimous nobles here...right?
        I_SAW_SOMEONE_SLINKING_THROUGH_THE_ALLEYWAYS_THE                              = 10509,  -- I saw someone slinking through the alleyways the other night. I could only describe him as a shady gent.
        ODD_I_KNOW_WHEN_I_ASKED_MY_SUPERIOR                                           = 10510,  -- Odd, I know. When I asked my superior about it, he told me people have spotted a guy fitting that description for years!
        I_H_H_HOPE_IT_S_NOT_A                                                         = 10511,  -- I h-h-hope it's not a ghost! I'm d-d-deathly afraid of ghosts! I can barely take a step without getting Galkabumps anymore.
        THIS_HOTEL_S_STAFF_IS_THE_ABSOLUTE_PARAGON                                    = 10512,  -- This hotel's staff is the absolute paragon of hospitality, I must say. What's more, the architecture and interior design surpass even the most opulent facilities I've previously had the pleasure of visiting.
        THE_ONLY_DOWNSIDE_TO_SURROUNDING_ONESELF_IN_SUCH                              = 10513,  -- The only downside to surrounding oneself in such luxury is that it depletes your life savings. With not a gil to my name, I must prowl the streets like a common beggar in search of suitable employment.
        I_TRIED_GETTING_AN_INTERVIEW_WITH_THE_FORMER                                  = 10514,  -- I tried getting an interview with the former royal family at Castle Adoulin, but they turned me down at the gates! Don't they understand that inquiring minds are desperate to know more about this historical household!?
        OH_WELL_AT_LEAST_I_VE_BEEN_ABLE                                               = 10515,  -- Oh well, at least I've been able to snatch up pieces of gossip around town. Maybe I can use that as a pretense to bag myself a rich broad. Heh heh.
        WHAT_IS_IT_I_HAVEN_T_THE_TIME                                                 = 10516,  -- What is it? I haven't the time to dawdle, you know. I'm meeting with some affluent merchants very soon.
        WE_RE_GOING_TO_DISCUSS_WHAT_NEEDS_MUST                                        = 10517,  -- We're going to discuss what needs must be met after the colonization effort has had some time to develop. The faster we read trends, the more money we'll make! Bwahaha!
        ALL_BIG_DREAMS_START_AS_SMALL_SEEDS_PLANT                                     = 10518,  -- All big dreams start as small seeds. Plant some of our seeds and watch your own dreams grow!
        UGH_DID_YOU_COME_HERE_FOR_THE_EXPRESS                                         = 10519,  -- Ugh, did you come here for the express purpose of ruining my vacation!?
        IF_I_D_HAVE_KNOWN_JUST_HOW_LOUD                                               = 10520,  -- If I'd have known just how loud you pioneers squawked, I'd be at my other house in the Far East instead!
        WELCOME_TO_ADOULIN_MON_AMI_AMIE_HAVE_YOU                                      = 10521,  -- Welcome to Adoulin, mon ami/amie]! Have you some business with moi this day?
        I_JUST_BUMPED_INTO_THIS_STRANGE_FELLOW_A                                      = 10522,  -- I just bumped into this strange fellow a few days ago. He said he came from a place called the Middle Lands.
        COULD_HE_POSSIBLY_BE_THE_ACCOMPLISHED_TECHNICIAN_ALL                          = 10523,  -- Could he possibly be the accomplished technician all the ladies around town are gossiping about? I believe they said his name was...Cid? No, that doesn't sound quite right...
        I_MADE_A_FORTUNE_HERE_IN_ULBUKA_SO                                            = 10524,  -- I made a fortune here in Ulbuka, so I decided to spend a little extra and dine at this restaurant everyone was praising.
        MUCH_TO_MY_DISMAY_THE_FOOD_WAS_ATROCIOUS                                      = 10525,  -- Much to my dismay, the food was atrocious, the atmosphere abysmal, and I could barely understand anything the chef said!
        I_LL_HAVE_TO_GET_STARTED_ON_MY                                                = 10526,  -- I'll have to get started on my next venture to rid myself of the bad taste that place left in my mouth.
        KNOW_YOU_THE_SILVER_KNIFE_SIR_MADAME_PIONEER                                  = 10527,  -- Know you the Silver Knife, Sir/Madame] Pioneer?
        IT_IS_A_SPECIAL_CLUB_WHICH_ONLY_THOSE                                         = 10528,  -- It is a special club which only those born with a silver spoon in their mouths may enter--I don't know why Knife, though. Sadly, even as a member of the Elvaan race, I lack the upbringing to gain access to the wonders within its walls.
        THIS_IMPRESSIVE_ESTATARU_BELONGS_TO_MELVIEN_DE_MALECROIX                      = 10529,  -- This impressive estataru belongs to Melvien de Malecroix, the minister of finance.
        DESPITE_FIERCE_OPPOSITION_FROM_MANY_IN_ADOULIN_HE                             = 10530,  -- Despite fierce opposition from many in Adoulin, he convinced the council to move forward with the colonization effort. The only reason-weason you're able to stay here is because of him, so he deserves your utmost respect.
        BUT_NOW_NONE_OF_US_WILL_EVER_SEE                                              = 10531,  -- But now...none of us will ever see him again. The horrors-worrors of the jungle know no bounds!
        I_HAD_ALWAYS_LONGED_TO_BECOME_AN_EXORCIST                                     = 10532,  -- I had always longed to become an exorcist at this priory. Ever since I was but a babe suckling on my mother's teat, I knew that this was my calling.
        AND_I_FINALLY_REALIZED_THAT_DREAM_RECENTLY_I                                  = 10533,  -- And I finally realized that dream recently! I have been completely absorbed in my training. No evil spirits will be spraying our citizenry with pea soup, not while I'm around!
        YOU_MAY_HAVE_ALREADY_HEARD_THIS_DURING_YOUR                                   = 10534,  -- You may have already heard this during your travels, but there was an incident at the Wake of the Lilies over in the Middle Lands not so long ago.
        I_CAN_ALREADY_PICTURE_THE_DAY_EVIL_SPIRITS                                    = 10535,  -- I can already picture the day evil spirits will descend upon this city en masse and suck the souls from the living, occupying their hollowed bodies and roaming the landscape for fresher flesh! It is for that day and that day alone we train... The power of Altana compels you!
        WITH_THE_ADVANCEMENT_OF_THE_COLONIZATION_EFFORT_PEOPLE                        = 10536,  -- With the advancement of the colonization effort, people have begun reporting sightings of crrryptic fiends darker than the most ominous shadow and often said to be harrrbingers of disaster.
        THESE_CRRREATURES_NAMED_UMBRILS_MAY_JUST_BE_THE                               = 10537,  -- These crrreatures, named umbrils, may just be the entities that the exorcists have been trrraining to combat all these years. At least that's what Vortimere tells us.
        THIS_EXTRAVAGANT_EDIFICE_IS_ONE_OF_THE_MANY                                   = 10538,  -- This extravagant edifice is one of the many assets held by our current minister of judication, Hildebert.
        HOWEVER_HILDEBERT_IS_AN_ASSIDUOUS_INDIVIDUAL_WHOSE_SERVICES                   = 10539,  -- However, Hildebert is an assiduous individual whose services are constantly in demand by the general public. As he rarely has the opportunity to return to his abode, he graciously allows Vortimere to occupy it.
        SHOULD_YOU_EVER_NEED_THE_COUNSEL_OF_EITHER                                    = 10540,  -- Should you ever need the counsel of either of these esteemed statesmen, this would be the place at which to seek it.
        THIS_IS_THE_MAINTENANCE_WAINTENANCE_TUNNEL_INTO_THE                           = 10541,  -- This is the maintenance-waintenance tunnel into the Rala Waterways. It's coalition policy not to let people wander down there, but we'll make an exception if you're willing to cooperate with us Peacekeepers.
        DESCEND_INTO_THE_RALA_WATERWAYS_YES_NO                                        = 10542,  -- Descend into the Rala Waterways? Yes. No.
        WHAT_D_YOU_SAY_YOUR_NAME_WAS_NEVER                                            = 10543,  -- What'd you say your name was? ...%? Never heard it before. Prrrobably because it's not worth hearing. Can you even name one herrroic feat you've accomplished here?
        YOUR_NAME_S_SOUNDS_VAGUELY_FAMILIAR_LIKE_SOME                                 = 10544,  -- Your name's...%? Sounds vaguely familiar, like some nonsense a derrranged beggar would mutter to himself in the alleyways.
        YOUR_NAME_S_IS_IT_SURRRPRISINGLY_ENOUGH_I                                     = 10545,  -- Your name's %, is it? Surrrprisingly enough, I do rrremember hearing it. Too bad I forget why.
        I_LL_ADMIT_THAT_SOME_PEOPLE_IN_ADOULIN                                        = 10546,  -- I'll admit that some people in Adoulin might know your name, but don't let that go to your head. You still haven't prrroven yourself one bit in my eyes.
        YOUR_NAME_S_MAKING_THE_RRROUNDS_IN_ADOULIN                                    = 10547,  -- Your name's making the rrrounds in Adoulin. I hear it on the lips of passersby rrrather often.
        MANY_ADOULINIANS_MARRRVEL_AT_WHAT_YOU_VE_DONE                                 = 10548,  -- Many Adoulinians marrrvel at what you've done. It won't be long before everyone in town knows your name.
        YOU_VE_BECOME_A_HOUSEHOLD_NAME_THRRROUGHOUT_THE                               = 10549,  -- You've become a household name thrrroughout the sacred city. Everyone's waiting to hear what amazing feats you'll purrrform next!
        YOU_VE_TRRRULY_GRABBED_YOUR_DREAMS_BY_THE                                     = 10550,  -- You've trrruly grabbed your dreams by the scruff and rrripped them from the paws of mediocrity! Not an hour passes without some maiden blushing over the mention of your name/man prrrofessing his love for you in the streets].
        YOUR_NAME_BELONGS_IN_THE_ANNALS_ALONGSIDE_AUGUST                              = 10551,  -- Your name belongs in the annals alongside August Adoulin's as an example of a trrrue hero. Don't let anyone tell you differently!
        OH_HAVE_YOU_COME_TO_INQUIRRRE_ABOUT_SOMETHING                                 = 10552,  -- Oh? Have you come to inquirrre about something?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_ASK_WHAT_S_MY_REPUTATION                                        = 10553,  -- What will you ask? What's my reputation like here? What's my coalition rank? Nothing.
        ADOULIN_S_ESTEEMED_COALITIONS_HAVE_GIVEN_YOU_THE                              = 10554,  -- Adoulin's esteemed coalitions have given you the following titles due to your supporrrt for their activities:
        S_COALITION_RANKS_PIONEERS_PEACEKEEPERS_COURIERS_SCOUTS_INVENTORS             = 10555,  -- %'s coalition ranks: Pioneers': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend]. Peacekeepers': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend]. Couriers': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend]. Scouts': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend]. Inventors': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend]. Mummers': [Petitioner/Probationer/Disciple/Contributor/Partner/Advisor/Magnate/Legend].
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_FURRRTHER_INFORMATION_YOU_ONLY_NEED                         = 10556,  -- Should you desire furrrther information, you only need inquire at the Civil Registrar located in the [./Pioneers'/Peacekeepers'/Couriers'/Scouts'/Inventors'/Mummers'] Coalition.
        I_AM_GRRREATLY_HONORED_TO_HAVE_SPOKEN_WITH                                    = 10557,  -- I am grrreatly honored to have spoken with a legendary pioneer such as yourself.
        STOP_LOITERING_IN_FRRRONT_OF_CASTLE_ADOULIN_OR                                = 10558,  -- Stop loitering in frrront of Castle Adoulin or I'll gouge your eyes out!
        MAY_I_HELP_YOU_YOU_WISH_FOR_ME                                                = 10559,  -- May I help you? ...You wish for me to announce your prrresence to Ikhi Askamot?
        ID_10560                                                                      = 10560,  -- %!
        NHILI_IS_A_GEOMANCER_JUST_LIKE_ME_PLEASE                                      = 10561,  -- Nhili, % is a geomancer, just like me. Please let us see Ikhi Askamot.
        AH_YES_DEARRR_SYLVIE_I_D_LOVE_TO                                              = 10562,  -- Ah, yes, dearrr Sylvie. I'd love to help, but she is quite busy these days...
        PLEASE_PLEASE_IT_S_A_MATTER_OF_LIFE                                           = 10563,  -- Please! Please! It's a matter of life or death!
        MY_GOODNESS_SYLVIE_DAAARLING_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING                               = 10564,  -- My goodness! Sylvie, daaarling, what are you doing way out here?
        LHAISO                                                                        = 10565,  -- Lhaiso!
        ARE_THOSE_TEARS_MY_PET_WHATEVER_COULD_BE                                      = 10566,  -- Are those...tears, my pet? Whatever could be wrong?
        WELL_THIS_IS_QUITE_THE_PICKLE_FOR_YOU                                         = 10567,  -- Well, this is quite the pickle for you then, no? To think, Hostenn missing, gone without a trace.
        A_GEOMANCER_GOING_MISSING_CAN_ONLY_MEAN_ONE                                   = 10568,  -- A geomancer going missing can only mean one thing--he has incurred the wrath of nature herself. Tragic.
        OH_DEAR_I_HAVE_PERHAPS_BEEN_A_BIT                                             = 10569,  -- Oh dear, I have perhaps been a bit harsh. I meant no ill will, I assure you.
        N_NO_IT_S_ALL_RIGHT_I_M                                                       = 10570,  -- N-no, it's all right. I'm just pleased that you understand how difficult this is for me.
        I_M_HERE_TO_ASK_FOR_IKHI_S                                                    = 10571,  -- I'm here to ask for Ikhi's aid--she's the reincarnation of the primal geomancer, Sih Renaye, right?
        BUT_IT_MUST_BE_FATE_THAT_BROUGHT_ME                                           = 10572,  -- But it must be fate that brought me to you, great Lhaiso. Finally, something's gone right.
        P_PLEASE_I_WANT_YOU_TO_HELP_DADDY                                             = 10573,  -- P-please! I want you to help Daddy!
        WHY_LITTLE_SYLVIE_OF_COURSE_I_UNDERSTAND_WHY                                  = 10574,  -- Why, little Sylvie, of course I understand why you would come to me. Your emotions have truly touched me, however...
        MY_BEST_DISCIPLE_IKHI_CANNOT_HELP_YOU_AND                                     = 10575,  -- My best disciple, Ikhi, cannot help you. And of course, that means my aid is absolutely out of the question.
        B_BUT_WHY                                                                     = 10576,  -- B-but...why?
        THE_LEGENDARY_SIH_RENAYE_BECAME_ONE_WITH_NATURE                               = 10577,  -- The legendary Sih Renaye became one with nature, causing rivers to change their course and trees to sprout tall in mere moments.
        AND_THEN_TOGETHER_WITH_HER_FIVE_DISCIPLES_SHE                                 = 10578,  -- And then, together with her five disciples, she prevailed over the ferocious Velkk.
        WHY_DO_YOU_SUPPOSE_THIS_IS_THIS_IS                                            = 10579,  -- Why do you suppose this is? This is simply a personal theory, dear, but I think it is because she was not actually a person.
        GREAT_LHAISO_WHY_DO_YOU_DEIGN_TO_SHARE                                        = 10580,  -- Great Lhaiso, why do you deign to share your thoughts with these outsiders?
        AND_SYLVIE_SURELY_YOUR_FATHER_S_COMPANIONS_ARE                                = 10581,  -- And Sylvie, surely your father's companions are out looking for him.
        IT_S_NOT_OUR_PLACE_TO_LOOK_FOR                                                = 10582,  -- It's not our place to look for him. He cast his lot with the pioneers, and so it is up to them to find him.
        SO_SYLVIE_DEAREST_SURELY_YOU_CAN_ACCEPT_OUR                                   = 10583,  -- So Sylvie, dearest, surely you can accept our position.
        I_I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_THIS_IS_BECAUSE                                             = 10584,  -- I-I can't believe... This is because I'm of Zacariah's blood, isn't it? Fine. I'll go look for him myself!
        OH_THE_SWEET_THING_HAS_GOT_IT_BACKWARDS                                       = 10585,  -- Oh, the sweet thing has got it backwards. Our desire to help her is without question--we just don't have the ability to do so.
        YOU_THERE_YES_YOU_I_CAN_SENSE_THAT                                            = 10586,  -- You there--yes, you. I can sense that you have a stronger bond with her than I--go in my stead and help save her father.
        HOSTENN_WAS_LAST_SEEN_IN_MORIMAR_BASALT_FIELDS                                = 10587,  -- Hostenn was last seen in Morimar Basalt Fields, was he not? Then someone at the frontier station there might be able to tell you more.
        SYLVIE_S_QUITE_BRRRASH_TO_HEAD_TO_MORIMAR                                     = 10588,  -- Sylvie's quite brrrash to head to Morimar Basalt Fields all by her lonesome. It would be terrible if some ill fate were to befall her, too.
        LHAISO_HAS_ORDERED_YOU_TO_GO_FIND_HER                                         = 10589,  -- Lhaiso has ordered you to go find her fatherrr, Hostenn. Her wishes must be respected.
        AND_IF_YOU_ARE_A_PIONEERRR_YOU_MUST                                           = 10590,  -- And if you are a pioneerrr, you must be intimately familiar with the area. The frontier station there can surely update you on the situation.
        OTHER_MEMBERS_OF_THE_ORDERRR_HAVE_TOLD_ME                                     = 10591,  -- Other members of the orderrr have told me that even though the great Lhaiso herself went to help Hostenn, he was unable to be saved.
        DESPITE_BEING_OF_THE_ZACARIAH_LINEAGE_HE_WAS                                  = 10592,  -- Despite being of the Zacariah lineage, he was a geomancer of the highest caliberrr. He shall be missed.
        AH_IKHI_ASKAMOT_AND_LHAISO_NEFTEREH_HAVE_BEEN                                 = 10593,  -- Ah, %... Ikhi Askamot and Lhaiso Neftereh have been waiting for you.
        I_AM_AFRRRAID_HOWEVER_THAT_LHAISO_HAS_TAKEN                                   = 10594,  -- I am afrrraid, however, that Lhaiso has taken ill. Please make your visit brrrief.
        LHAISO_FORGIVE_MY_IMPUDENCE_BUT_I_MUST_BE                                     = 10595,  -- Lhaiso, forgive my impudence, but I must be frank.
        YOU_MAY_HAVE_FALLEN_ILL_BECAUSE_THE_HIGHER                                    = 10596,  -- You may have fallen ill because the higher power is angered at your assistance of the blood of the betrayer.
        I_DISAGREE_THE_HIGHER_POWER_WOULD_NOT_CASTIGATE                               = 10597,  -- I disagree. The higher power would not castigate her just because we aided another.
        NO_WHAT_S_MORE_LIKELY_IS_THAT_THE                                             = 10598,  -- No, what's more likely is that the betrayer's descendant poisoned her.
        AND_LHAISO_WHAT_DO_YOU_THINK                                                  = 10599,  -- And Lhaiso, what do you think?
        I_CANNOT_QUITE_PUT_MY_FINGER_ON_IT                                            = 10600,  -- I cannot quite put my finger on it...but it probably has to do with our total inability to stop the colonization of Ulbuka.
        LOOK_WHO_IT_IS_ONE_OF_THE_PIONEERS                                            = 10601,  -- Look who it is! One of the pioneers who caused all this trouble to begin with!
        THIS_IS_WHY_I_WAS_COMPLETELY_OPPOSED_TO                                       = 10602,  -- This is why I was completely opposed to sharing the powers of the geomancer with one so intent on pillaging and defiling the land.
        THAT_S_ENOUGH_OUT_OF_YOU_ALL_THIS                                             = 10603,  -- That's enough out of you all. This man/woman] is a guest of ourrrs.
        FORGIVE_ME_FOR_NOT_BEING_ABLE_TO_GIVE                                         = 10604,  -- Forgive me for not being able to give you a proper greeting, %.
        LHAISO_USED_THE_POWER_OF_THE_COMMUNION_TO                                     = 10605,  -- Lhaiso used the power of the Communion to converse with something greater than us...the higher power...
        I_SUPPOSE_I_AM_SO_TIRED_BECAUSE_THE                                           = 10606,  -- I suppose I am so tired because the spell took the wind out of my sails.
        I_CALLED_YOU_TO_THIS_MANSE_TODAY_BECAUSE                                      = 10607,  -- %, I called you to this manse today because I have something to bequeath unto you.
        IS_IT_WISE_TO_ENTRUST_THIS_ONE_WITH                                           = 10608,  -- Is it wise to entrust this one with something so precious?
        HERE_FOR_YOU                                                                  = 10609,  -- Here...for you.
        MANY_ASSERT_THAT_IT_WAS_A_GRAVE_MISTAKE                                       = 10610,  -- Many assert that it was a grave mistake for geomancers to have lent their aid to the colonization effort.
        BUT_IKHI_AND_I_WERE_BOTH_IN_ACCORD                                            = 10611,  -- But Ikhi and I were both in accord that this issue of opening up the continent is one that should be resolved with the pioneers, not in spite of them.
        NATURE_THE_HIGHER_POWER_HAS_STRRRIVEN_FOR_EONS                                = 10612,  -- Nature--the higher power--has strrriven for eons to reconcile the irreconcilable within her loving embrace.
        WE_TOO_MUST_FOLLOW_HER_EXAMPLE                                                = 10613,  -- We, too, must follow her example.
        AS_BOTH_A_PIONEER_AND_A_GEOMANCER_YOU                                         = 10614,  -- As both a pioneer and a geomancer, you stand at the crossroads of two disparate worlds.
        I_HOPE_MY_DEAR_THAT_YOU_WILL_CONTINUE                                         = 10615,  -- I hope, my dear, that you will continue to work with us to find an answer.
        THE_GREAT_LHAISO_S_CONDITION_GROWS_INCREASINGLY_GRRRAVE                       = 10616,  -- The great Lhaiso's condition grows increasingly grrrave by the day. I cannot help but harbor a dark sense of foreboding.
        AND_SYLVIE_YOU_COME_AT_THE_PURRRFECT_TIME                                     = 10617,  -- %...and Sylvie! You come at the purrrfect time. Lhaiso has been asking for you.
        PLEASE_GO_RIGHT_IN_AND_WHEN_YOU_RRRETURN                                      = 10618,  -- Please, go right in...and when you rrreturn, allow me to inquire as to her physical state.
        FOR_YOU_SEE_SHE_HAS_SHUT_HERSELF_IN                                           = 10619,  -- For you see, she has shut herself in her room and rrrefuses to allow even her most trusted servants entry.
        YOU_IN_PARTICULARRR_HAVE_PIQUED_HER_INTEREST_PLEASE                           = 10620,  -- %... You in particularrr have piqued her interest. Please, make sure she is well.
        SYLVIE_THANK_YOU_FOR_COMING                                                   = 10621,  -- Sylvie... %... Thank you for coming.
        LHAISO_A_ARE_YOU_ALL_RIGHT                                                    = 10622,  -- Lhaiso! A-are you all right?
        THERE_IS_SOMETHING_I_NEED_TO_SHARE_AND                                        = 10623,  -- There is something...I need to share. And I know that the two of you would understand me more easily than anyone else.
        FORGIVE_ME_FOR_CUTTING_TO_THE_QUICK_BUT                                       = 10624,  -- Forgive me for cutting to the quick, but my body is quite frail of late.
        BACK_IN_THE_BASALT_FIELDS_WHEN_I_USED                                         = 10625,  -- Back in the basalt fields...when I used the primal geomancer's bell...
        I_THINK_THAT_WHEN_I_CALLED_OUT_TO                                             = 10626,  -- I think that when I called out to nature, I awoke the higher power that had been sleeping within Adoulin for eons.
        WE_HAVE_INCURRED_ITS_WRATH_BY_THE_WAY                                         = 10627,  -- We have incurred its wrath--by the way we have destroyed nature with every step we make into Ulbuka.
        JUST_THE_OTHER_NIGHT_WHEN_I_BEGAN_TO                                          = 10628,  -- Just the other night, when I began to ring the fabled bell...
        WHY_DOST_THOU_THINK_GEOMANCERS_ARE_AWARE_OF                                   = 10629,  -- <Why dost thou think geomancers are aware of the lifestream and able to manipulate the forces of Indi and Geo?>
        THOU_APPEAREST_TO_BE_OF_THE_MIND_THAT                                         = 10630,  -- <Thou appearest to be of the mind that thy control over the lifestream is due to thy dedication and research.>
        IT_IS_CONTEMPTIBLE_BEYOND_COMPARE_THAT_THOU_HAST                              = 10631,  -- <It is contemptible beyond compare that thou hast forgotten why we bequeathed this power to thee.>
        CHILDREN_OF_ALTANA_THOU_SEEKEST_NAUGHT_BUT_DESTRUCTION                        = 10632,  -- <Children of Altana, thou seekest naught but destruction. We have always faced thee with fear and trepidation.>
        THY_KIND_HATH_FORGOTTEN_THAT_THOU_ART_BUT                                     = 10633,  -- <Thy kind hath forgotten that thou art but one speck of a greater whole, and thus seek to leave thine indelible mark upon our flesh.>
        YET_SIH_WAS_DIFFERENT_SIH_BELIEVED_THAT_HUMANITY                              = 10634,  -- <Yet Sih was different. Sih believed that humanity's calling was to respect and understand us, and she felt that thy kind could carry out this most noble of goals.>
        I_KNOW_PERHAPS_MORE_THAN_ANYONE_ELSE_THAT                                     = 10635,  -- I know, perhaps more than anyone else, that it was our fault that the pioneering initiative was not stopped.
        BUT_PLEASE_HEAR_ME_OUT_PIONEERING_IS_A                                        = 10636,  -- But please, hear me out--pioneering is a must if Adoulin is to survive!
        AS_THE_HEIR_TO_THE_PRIMAL_GEOMANCER_SIH                                       = 10637,  -- As the heir to the primal geomancer Sih Renaye's legacy, I have come to this conclusion even in light of the respect and understanding I have for nature!
        I_KNOW_THAT_WE_MUST_PRESS_ON_IF                                               = 10638,  -- I know that we must press on...if we are to live to see another century.
        THOU_DOST_SPEAK_LIKE_HE_DID_LIKE_ZACARIAH                                     = 10639,  -- <Thou dost speak like he did... Like Zacariah did... Then thou art upholding the oath we made him swear in centuries past. Prove thy dedication...in the land where he resides.>
        THAT_IS_WHAT_THE_HIGHER_POWER_TOLD_ME                                         = 10640,  -- That is what the higher power told me...and I am no longer able to ring this most sacred of bells.
        N_NO                                                                          = 10641,  -- N-no...
        YET_I_AM_NOT_THE_ONLY_ONE_IKHI                                                = 10642,  -- Yet I am not the only one. Ikhi was unable to call forth its power as well. She has gathered the other geomancers of our order in an attempt to perform the Communion...
        BUT_THEY_WILL_SURELY_FAIL_THAT_IS_WHY                                         = 10643,  -- But they will surely fail. That is why I called the two of you.
        WHAT_THE_HIGHER_POWER_TAUGHT_TO_ZACARIAH_IT                                   = 10644,  -- What the higher power taught to Zacariah...it was how to become one with the lifestream, was it not?
