        SOUNDS_LIKE_A_CASE_OF_IF_YOU_DON                                              = 11118,  -- Sounds like a case of If you don't have anything nice to say, don't say anything. Okay, out it goes. Next!
        SOMEONE_SLOW_THE_AIRSHIP_TO_PESSIMISMVILLE_YOU_RE                             = 11119,  -- Someone slow the airship to pessimismville! You're either the most negative person I've met in my life or you're trying to pull my leg. Trying being the operative word here.
        FOOL_ME_ONCE_SHAME_ON_YOU_FOOL_ME                                             = 11120,  -- Fool me once, shame on you. Fool me again and...well, you're not gonna fool me again! Let's start over from the top...and be serious this time!
        IN_THE_YEAR_350_A_DEEP_SEATED_CONFLICT                                        = 11121,  -- In the year 350, a deep-seated conflict over political control of the archipelago erupted, embroiling each of the Adoulinian orders.
        THE_FOUNDER_KING_S_LAST_WORDS_TO_HIS                                          = 11122,  -- The founder king's last words to his people began to lose their efficacy circa Crystal Era 400. Though the populace once deathly feared entering the jungle, they then declared that colonization would begin anew.
        THE_YEAR_WAS_CRYSTAL_ERA_405_AFTER_THE                                        = 11123,  -- The year was Crystal Era 405. After the ban on entering the Ulbukan hinterland was lifted, a certain artist gathered his tools of the trade and marched into the heart of the jungle. Once there, he became enamored with the local flora--one gargantuan tree in particular--and thus painted one of the most vivid and influential scenes in the history of the west.
        AFTER_DEPARTING_ON_A_LONG_AND_ARDUOUS_JOURNEY                                 = 11124,  -- After departing on a long and arduous journey across multiple continents and laying eyes upon myriad wonders, Sverdhried finally managed to make landfall in Adoulin sometime during the first half of the fifth century.
        COINCIDING_WITH_THE_ADVANCEMENT_OF_THE_COLONIZATION_EFFORT                    = 11125,  -- Coinciding with the advancement of the colonization effort and the advent of Crystal Era 550, the earth began to shake mightily at irregular intervals. Fissures gaped wide and whole topographical features were reformed when these manifestations of terric vengeance struck.
        IN_THE_YEAR_607_DOMESTICATED_GIANT_SHEEP_WERE                                 = 11126,  -- In the year 607, domesticated giant sheep were exported to the Middle Lands in hope of both diversifying its breadbasket and enhancing Adoulin's mercantile prowess.
        RECORDS_EXIST_OF_A_BAFFLING_INCIDENT_WHERE_NOT                                = 11127,  -- Records exist of a baffling incident where not just one tree, but whole swaths of woodlands matured over the course of a single nightfall in the early part of the seventh century. Certain academics hold that the event described within such documents is specious at best, but their sheer volume leads most to believe their veracity.
        ID_879_IS_CITED_AS_THE_YEAR_IN_WHICH                                          = 11128,  -- 879 is cited as the year in which produce cultivation first began within the Civic Arboretum. Harnessing the power of irrigation, which was made possible thanks to its location in the Rala Waterways, Adoulinian researchers have been able to raise crops that help alleviate the food shortage plaguing this municipality.
        DUPLICATES_OF_A_PAINTING_CONSIDERED_ALMOST_SACROSANCT_BY                      = 11129,  -- Duplicates of a painting considered almost sacrosanct by the art community infiltrated the market starting in 883. While extremely faithful to the original's depiction of a colossal tree guarding the Ulbukan frontier, the condition of the paints used and the type of brush strokes employed make it easy to discern their lack of authenticity.
        MULTIPLE_PEOPLE_HAVE_SPOTTED_A_CRYPTIC_MALE_PATRONIZING                       = 11130,  -- Multiple people have spotted a cryptic male patronizing the Mummers' Coalition throughout the year 884. Who he is and why he spends so much time at a house of amusement remain a mystery, and perhaps will for eternity.
        HOW_S_THAT_SOUND_TO_YOU                                                       = 11131,  -- How's that sound to you?
        I_D_GO_SO_FAR_AS_TO_SAY                                                       = 11132,  -- I'd go so far as to say that it's the pinnacle of relevancy and eon-defining aural ecstasy. Eon-defining being the operative word here.
        HOW_S_IT_SOUND_TO_YOU_LIKE_A                                                  = 11133,  -- How's it sound to you? Like a faithful rendition of a sonata. Like a discordant cacophony.
        R_REALLY_I_TRULY_THOUGHT_I_HAD_SOMETHING                                      = 11134,  -- R-really!? I truly thought I had something there. Well, let's go back to the drawing board in a bit.
        I_M_GLAD_TO_HEAR_WE_RE_ON                                                     = 11135,  -- I'm glad to hear we're on the same page, hohoho! Let me pass this on to the Couriers' Coalition and we'll be good to go. If only I knew exactly who my employer was, I could send it directly, but...
        WHO_CARES_ABOUT_WHERE_I_GET_MY_MONEY                                          = 11136,  -- Who cares about where I get my money from, as long as it's enough to make Yocile swoon for me!
