        I_AM_NOTHING_IF_NOT_FORGIVING_THOUGH_I                                        = 12613,  -- I am nothing if not forgiving, though. I shall give you a chance to redeem yourself whenever you see fit--if you can fit it into your busy schedule, that is.
        I_SENSE_AN_OMINOUS_FORCE_INTERFERING_WITH_YOUR                                = 12614,  -- I sense an ominous force interfering with your progress... Could it be the [/warrior/monk/white mage/black mage/red mage/thief/paladin/dark knight/beastmaster/bard/ranger/samurai/ninja/dragoon/summoner/blue mage/corsair/puppetmaster/dancer/scholar/geomancer/rune fencer] within you!?
        YOUR_TH_ATTEMPT_AND_WE_RE_STILL_NO                                            = 12615,  -- Your #th attempt and we're still no closer than before? Perhaps 'tis I who needs to train more, so I don't accidentally give the talentless dreams they can never accomplish.
        I_WAS_UNDER_THE_IMPRESSION_THAT_YOU_WERE                                      = 12616,  -- I was under the impression that you were an adventurer renowned throughout the Middle Lands. Apparently that appellation amounts to little more than kindling for the fires of one's boasting.
        MY_CONDOLENCES_SIR_MADAME                                                     = 12617,  -- ...My condolences, sir/madame].
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_QUIT_WHILE_YOU_STILL                                            = 12618,  -- Why don't you quit while you still have your health? Many people would commit atrocities for a body as hale and hearty as yours.
        LET_ME_SAY_THIS_ONE_THING_YOU_MAY                                             = 12619,  -- Let me say this one thing: you may think you're special, but you're just as special as everyone else...that is to say, not at all.
        I_LOST_HOPE_FOR_YOU_LONG_AGO_BUT                                              = 12620,  -- I lost hope for you long ago, but this is already your #th time. Any further attempts would be a waste of time for us both.
        ZZZ                                                                           = 12621,  -- Zzz...
        I_VE_HAD_ENOUGH_OF_YOUR_INCOMPETENCE_LET                                      = 12622,  -- I've had enough of your incompetence! Let me spell this out loud and clear: y-o-u c-a-n-n-o-t u-s-e r-u-n-e-s!
        I_MIGHT_AS_WELL_STICK_AROUND_TO_SEE                                           = 12623,  -- I might as well stick around to see if you can make it an even #.
        Y_YOUR_ST_TRY                                                                 = 12624,  -- Y-your #st try!?
        PREPOSTEROUS_I_KNOW_MY_INTUITION_HAS_BEEN_FINELY                              = 12625,  -- Preposterous! I know my intuition has been finely honed over years of careful practice, but never in my wildest dreams did I think it would be so precise!
        IT_LOOKS_AS_IF_MY_EYES_KNOW_A                                                 = 12626,  -- It looks as if my eyes know a potential rune fencer when they see one. What an accomplishment, to complete this most arduous of tasks on attempt number #!
        SUCCESS_ON_ONLY_ATTEMPT_NUMBER_I_KNEW_YOU                                     = 12627,  -- Success on only attempt number #...? I knew you had it in you! Great job.
        IT_TOOK_YOU_EXACTLY_TRIES_TO_EXACT_YOUR                                       = 12628,  -- It took you exactly # tries to exact your victory. Well done...but I must admit you could also have done much better.
        IT_TOOK_YOU_ALL_THE_WAY_TO_ATTEMPT                                            = 12629,  -- It took you all the way to attempt number #? My spleen must be producing a surplus of its humor, for I can sadly muster nothing but a melancholy response to your performance.
        I_CANNOT_SAY_MUCH_OF_YOUR_TALENTS_YET                                         = 12630,  -- I cannot say much of your talents yet, but your unrelenting nature rivals that of even the hardest diamonds. It takes a special type of man/woman] to make it all the way to attempt number #.
        CONGRATULATIONS_ON_FINALLY_BECOMING_A_RUNE_FENCER_YOU                         = 12631,  -- Congratulations on finally becoming a rune fencer. You refused to think of yourself as refuse and have come out better for it. I look forward to the day when your true talents shine forth.
        I_APOLOGIZE_IF_MY_WORDS_LEFT_YOU_STRESSED                                     = 12632,  -- I apologize if my words left you stressed instead of soothed.
        I_CONTEND_THAT_MY_INTENTIONS_WERE_TRULY_ALTRUISTIC                            = 12633,  -- I contend that my intentions were truly altruistic.
        BY_THE_BY_LET_ME_CONGRATULATE_YOU_ONCE                                        = 12634,  -- By the by, let me congratulate you once more. I may have been the fertilizer to your flower, but you would never have been able to blossom without your own ability.
        I_ASSUME_THE_WORLD_LOOKS_SLIGHTLY_DIFFERENT_TO                                = 12635,  -- I assume the world looks slightly different to you now, seeing it through the eyes of a rune fencer.
        WHAT_S_THAT_HOW_LONG_UNTIL_THE_RUNES                                          = 12636,  -- What's that? How long until the runes' effects wear off?
        YOU_NEED_NOT_WORRY_ABOUT_THAT_FOR_IT                                          = 12637,  -- You need not worry about that, for it was simply a fallacy I perpetuated.
        I_WANTED_TO_SEE_IF_YOU_HAD_THE                                                = 12638,  -- I wanted to see if you had the fire in your belly to brave the searing pain of inscription and your defeats in heated combat that are sure to come eventually.
        FURTHERMORE_EVEN_SOMEONE_AS_LOQUACIOUS_AS_ME_DOESN                            = 12639,  -- Furthermore, even someone as loquacious as me doesn't have time to spend on every adventurer just looking to impress his/her] comrades.
        AT_ANY_RATE_ALLOW_ME_TO_REITERATE_YOUR                                        = 12640,  -- At any rate, allow me to reiterate: your runic powers will not dissipate under any circumstances.
        HOWEVER_THAT_DOES_NOT_MEAN_YOU_SHOULDN_T                                      = 12641,  -- However, that does not mean you shouldn't practice what you've learned. While yet unrefined, your power will prove quite useful in your quest to cultivate the wilds of Ulbuka.
        TIS_SAID_THAT_SVERDHRIED_THE_FATHER_OF_RUNIC                                  = 12642,  -- 'Tis said that Sverdhried, the father of runic inscription, created manifold techniques that were all based off his experiences in battle. I look forward to seeing how closely you replicate his success.
        ON_THAT_NOTE_I_BELIEVE_THE_TIME_HAS                                           = 12643,  -- On that note, I believe the time has come to present you with this.
        TIS_A_PRACTICE_BLADE_USED_BY_EVERY_RUNE                                       = 12644,  -- 'Tis %, a practice blade used by every rune fencer in the world. Just remember that while the sword may choose the rune fencer, 'tis the rune fencer who swings the sword, and not the other way around.
        ENJOY_WHAT_IS_TO_COME_GOOD_SIR_FAIR                                           = 12645,  -- Enjoy what is to come, good sir/fair lady], and may you be even stronger the next time we meet.
        RUNE_GAME_SETTINGS_LEAVE_IT_TO_YOURSELF_SUCCEED                               = 12646,  -- Rune game settings. Leave it to yourself. Succeed. Fail.
        WHO_RE_YOU_I_DON_T_KNOW_YOU                                                   = 12647,  -- Who're you? I don't know you! I can't entrust this harrowing mission of unfathomable secrecy to one whose name means less than sputum to me. Begone!
        I_VE_HEARD_MUCH_OF_YOUR_EXPLOITS_YOU                                          = 12648,  -- ...I've heard much of your exploits. You may just be competent enough to handle this.
        LET_S_KEEP_THIS_BRIEF_I_DON_T                                                 = 12649,  -- Let's keep this brief. I don't want anyone getting suspicious. I'm from the Armathrwn Society, and I've been dispatched to conduct analyses for Jeuno.
        OUR_SUBJECTS_THE_NAAKUALS                                                     = 12650,  -- Our subjects? The Naakuals.
        UGH_HOW_CAN_YOU_NOT_KNOW_OF_THEM                                              = 12651,  -- Ugh, how can you not know of them!? And I wanted to keep this brief...
        THE_NAAKUALS_ARE_THE_FIERCEST_MONSTROSITIES_TO_EVER                           = 12652,  -- The Naakuals are the fiercest monstrosities to ever prowl Eastern Ulbuka.
        WHILE_OUR_ORGANIZATION_LENDS_AID_TO_ADOULIN_AS                                = 12653,  -- While our organization lends aid to Adoulin as pioneers, our true purpose is to study these beasts. The problem is that we can't field enough men to do so.
        WE_VE_BEEN_ABLE_TO_PINPOINT_THEIR_LAIRS                                       = 12654,  -- We've been able to pinpoint their lairs, but we have no intelligence on their behavior when provoked.
        WITH_YOUR_HELP_THOUGH_WE_HOPE_TO_REMEDY                                       = 12655,  -- With your help, though, we hope to remedy that.
        LET_ME_GET_THIS_OUT_OF_THE_WAY                                                = 12656,  -- Let me get this out of the way now. You'll get no reward whatsoever.
        AT_LEAST_FROM_US                                                              = 12657,  -- ...At least from us.
        WE_RE_CONCERNED_WITH_INFORMATION_NOT_RICHES_YOU                               = 12658,  -- We're concerned with information, not riches. You can have whatever trinkets they're hoarding.
        THEY_RE_SOME_OF_THE_MOST_POWERFUL_BEASTS                                      = 12659,  -- They're some of the most powerful beasts that we know of, so they probably have something that'll catch your eye.
        THE_NAAKUALS_AREN_T_SOME_COMMON_BREED_OF                                      = 12660,  -- The Naakuals aren't some common breed of animal to be found in every home on the continent. Their dwellings are nigh impossible to find by normal means.
        I_DON_T_HAVE_TIME_TO_GO_INTO                                                  = 12661,  -- I don't have time to go into the details, but we've created devices that skirt the issue and track them down for you.
        ONCE_YOU_CROSS_INTO_THEIR_TERRITORY_THOUGH_THE                                = 12662,  -- Once you cross into their territory, though, the devices cease to function.
        YES_THOSE_RE_ALL_WE_VE_GOT_THEY                                               = 12663,  -- Yes, those're all we've got! They're also your only option for finding the Naakuals. These things don't come cheap, either, so start reaching into your pockets.
        GIL_IS_USELESS_FOR_OBTAINING_THE_NECESSARY_MATERIALS                          = 12664,  -- Gil is useless for obtaining the necessary materials around here, so I'll be needing payment in bayld.
        SO_WHAT_S_IT_GOING_TO_BE                                                      = 12665,  -- So, what's it going to be?
        WHAT_WILL_IT_BE_COUNT_ME_IN_GIMME                                             = 12666,  -- What will it be? Count me in! Gimme all needed items I don't have! Gimme a device! Tell me more about the devices. I need to hear that again. Count me out for now.
        THEN_TELL_NO_ONE_OF_WHAT_TRANSPIRED_HERE                                      = 12667,  -- Then tell no one of what transpired here. Now, away with you!
        THE_SOCIETY_APPRECIATES_YOUR_HELP_HERE_TAKE_THIS                              = 12668,  -- The society appreciates your help. Here, take this % with you.
        IT_WILL_ACT_AS_OUR_SURROGATE_AND_RECORD                                       = 12669,  -- It will act as our surrogate and record the information pertinent to our studies. I'll personally kill you if you lose it.
        I_SHOULDN_T_TALK_THIS_MUCH_SOMEONE_MIGHT                                      = 12670,  -- I shouldn't talk this much. Someone might see us. ...Don't ever make me do this again.
        WHICH_ONE_DO_YOU_NEED                                                         = 12671,  -- Which one do you need?
        WHICH_ONE_DO_YOU_NEED_BAYLD_BAYLD_BAYLD                                       = 12672,  -- Which one do you need? %. (# bayld) %. (# bayld) %. (# bayld) %. (# bayld) %. (# bayld) %. (# bayld) None.
        SHOW_ME_BAYLD_AND_WE_CAN_TALK                                                 = 12673,  -- %? Show me # bayld and we can talk.
        GIVE_HIM_THE_BAYLD_MIGHT_AS_WELL_NO                                           = 12674,  -- Give him the bayld? Might as well. No.
        YOU_RE_MISSING_A_TOTAL_OF_ITEM_WHICH                                          = 12675,  -- You're missing a total of # item[/s], which cost[s/] a grand sum of # bayld.
        PROCEED_BAYLD_YES_NO                                                          = 12676,  -- Proceed? (# bayld) Yes. No.
        THIS_SHOULD_BE_EVERYTHING_GO_FORTH_AND_FIGHT                                  = 12677,  -- This should be everything. Go forth and fight for the good of the city!
        QUIT_FOOLING_AROUND_THIS_ISN_T_A_GAME                                         = 12678,  -- Quit fooling around! This isn't a game, you hear!? Time is of the essence, so give me the right amount of bayld.
        TAKE_IT_AND_BE_ON_YOUR_WAY_YOU                                                = 12679,  -- Take it and be on your way. You never met with me, remember.
        TAKE_THEM_AND_BE_ON_YOUR_WAY_YOU                                              = 12680,  -- Take them and be on your way. You never met with me, remember.
        MAKE_IT_QUICK_AND_ACT_LIKE_WE_RE                                              = 12681,  -- Make it quick...and act like we're talking about the weather or something. Now, which do you need to know about?
        ABOUT_WHICH_DO_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_NONE                                          = 12682,  -- About which do you need to know? %. %. %. %. %. %. None.
        THE_LEADS_YOU_TO_THE_LAIR_OF_IN                                               = 12683,  -- The % leads you to the lair of [Colkhab, the Matriarch Naakual/Tchakka, the Riptide Naakual/Achuka, the Firebrand Naakual/Yumcax, the Ligneous Naakual/Hurkan, the Booming Naakual/Kumhau, the Flashfrost Naakual], in [Ceizak Battlegrounds/Foret de Hennetiel/Morimar Basalt Fields/Yorcia Weald/Marjami Ravine/Kamihr Drifts].
        YOU_MAY_ONLY_HAVE_AUDIENCE_WITH_THIS_TESTY                                    = 12684,  -- You may only have audience with this testy queen once you pass through a grove with thorns so sharp that they've claimed many an unguarded limb.
        COVER_YOURSELF_IN_THIS_NET_FOR_PROTECTION_YOU                                 = 12685,  -- Cover yourself in this net for protection. You'll never be able to withstand the bushes that guard the entrance otherwise.
        THE_LAIR_OF_THIS_AQUATIC_LANCER_LIES_ON                                       = 12686,  -- The lair of this aquatic lancer lies on the far bank of the Zoldeff River. You'll need to be sufficiently skilled at piloting watercraft in order to reach it.
        THIS_WHICH_USES_THE_SAME_TECHNOLOGY_AS_AIRSHIPS                               = 12687,  -- This %, which uses the same technology as airships, will take you where you need to go. Sadly, the forces emitted by Naakuals' lairs will destroy it once you get too close.
        THAT_SHOULDN_T_MATTER_THOUGH_YOU_WON_T                                        = 12688,  -- That shouldn't matter, though. You won't have any more use for it once you get there anyway.
        THE_LAIR_OF_THIS_MAGMA_BELCHING_BEHEMOTH_IS                                   = 12689,  -- The lair of this magma-belching behemoth is closed off by scorching hot boulders.
        EQUIP_THIS_ARMOR_WITH_HEAT_RESISTANT_PROPERTIES_AND                           = 12690,  -- Equip this armor with heat-resistant properties and you should last long enough to at least be stomped to a paste.
        THE_DEBUGGERY_FAME_ON_FAME_OFF_IT_S                                           = 12691,  -- The Debuggery Fame ON! Fame OFF! It's my first time. My sophomore attempt. Accepted that quest! The Event Begins.
        YOU_LL_NEVER_HAVE_A_CHANCE_TO_LAY                                             = 12692,  -- You'll never have a chance to lay eyes on this airborne arbor unless you're able to part the throng of overgrown trees that stifles your path.
        THEY_DO_LITTLE_TO_INSPIRE_FEAR_IN_THOSE                                       = 12693,  -- They do little to inspire fear in those who approach them, but not a single surveyor I've talked to who left without carrying a special growth retardant has come back as sane as he left. Honestly, I wouldn't either after seeing three trees rise up for every one I chopped down.
        THE_EFFECTS_OF_THE_FORMULA_MAY_BE_STRONG                                      = 12694,  -- The effects of the formula may be strong, but it won't leave a lasting impact on the surrounding environs. The actual tree you douse with it, though? You won't even be able to use it for kindling.
        THIS_AVIAN_MONSTROSITY_S_DEN_ISN_T_TOO                                        = 12695,  -- This avian monstrosity's den isn't too hard to discern, what with all the vines digging into the sheer cliff that leads up to it.
        A_LAD_LASS_AS_SMART_AS_YOU_PROBABLY                                           = 12696,  -- A lad/lass] as smart as you probably knows this already, but you'll need to learn how to scale these vines and render the saber-like thorns that protrude from them harmless.
        REGRETTABLY_THE_THORNS_AREN_T_THE_BIGGEST_OF                                  = 12697,  -- Regrettably, the thorns aren't the biggest of your worries. Hurkan's called the Booming Naakual for a reason, and even the vines that guard his roost ring with the terrible sound of thunder and shock those foolish enough to touch them without a dampening agent.
        I_SHOULD_CAUTION_YOU_THAT_WHILE_THIS_MIXTURE                                  = 12698,  -- I should caution you that while this mixture does away with electrical charges exceptionally fast, it only lasts about as long as it will take for you to climb the vines. I also can't recommend using it in quick succession.
        THIS_ICE_BEAST_S_STOMPING_GROUNDS_SHOULDN_T                                   = 12699,  -- This ice beast's stomping grounds shouldn't be hard to discern, for they're marked by a conglomeration of snow that stretches high enough to bury the valley in which it resides.
        CLIMBING_THIS_PALISADE_OF_PRECIPITATION_IS_ONE_THING                          = 12700,  -- Climbing this palisade of precipitation is one thing, but the land's topography also creates some harrowingly strong winds that've left countless frozen corpses scattered in pieces across its ridges.
        IF_YOU_WANT_TO_EVEN_GET_NEAR_THE                                              = 12701,  -- If you want to even get near the foot of it, you'll need this mountaineering set. It should keep you insulated against the harsh, biting winds and arctic temperatures as well as tethered to the ground.
        EACH_INDIVIDUAL_PIECE_OF_CLOTHING_IN_THE_SET                                  = 12702,  -- Each individual piece of clothing in the set is woven with rare and experimental fibers that increases the production of body heat, then retain it to an astounding degree. We say it's experimental, though, because the effect only lasts long enough to get you over the hump and into the lion's den.
        I_AIN_T_NEVER_SEEN_NO_WHIPPERSNAPPER_WITH                                     = 12703,  -- I ain't never seen no whippersnapper with your face in these parts. Say...mightn't ya've come across any simulacrum segments while ya were out thwick-thwackin' through Eastern Ulbuka?
        WHAT_YOU_SAY_SONNY_MISSY_YOU_AIN_T                                            = 12704,  -- What you say, sonny/missy]? You ain't know what simulacrum segments are!?
        WELL_THEY_S_THREE_OF_A_KIND_YOU                                               = 12705,  -- Well, they's three of a kind. You've got your heads, your torsos, and your legs. Puttin' 'em t'gether's the 'ard part, though. Most young'uns say they ain't got no time to learn 'ow.
        ME_THOUGH_I_VE_GOT_ALL_THE_TIME                                               = 12706,  -- Me, though? I've got all the time in the world. In fact, my middle name be Time. Wait, but what was my last name...?
        ANYWAY_I_MAKES_MY_LIVIN_OFF_TINKERIN_WITH                                     = 12707,  -- Anyway, I makes my livin' off tinkerin' with simulacra. I'd be 'appy to build one for ya if you're willin' to slip me somethin' in return and listen to how I dun fished up a doozy of a craklaw once!
        YA_AIN_T_GOTTA_DOUBT_ME_NONE_WITH                                             = 12708,  -- Ya ain't gotta doubt me none with them eyes of yours, little lad/lass]. I know these're your prop'ty. I ain't gon' steal 'em.
        IF_YA_APPEN_UPON_SOME_SIMULACRUM_SEGMENTS_IN                                  = 12709,  -- If ya 'appen upon some simulacrum segments in the wilds of Eastern Ulbuka, couldja make an ol' man with nothin' better to do 'appy and gimme some to tinker with?
        HEY_I_REMEMBER_YOU_YOU_RE_SMEIRDLIN_RIGHT                                     = 12710,  -- Hey, I remember you! You're...Smeirdlin, right? What's on the docket today?
        WELL_WELL_WELL_WELL_WELL_WELL_WELL_LOOKIT                                     = 12711,  -- Well, well, well, well, well, well, well! Lookit what we've got 'ere... A natural collector, you.
        IFF_N_YOU_LL_BE_NEEDIN_THAT_SLAPPED                                           = 12712,  -- Iff'n you'll be needin' that slapped t'gether or whatnot, just slip it into these shaky hands o' mine.
        WHY_COLOR_ME_COCKEYED_YOU_VE_GOT_SOME                                         = 12713,  -- Why, color me cockeyed! You've got some obsidian fragments on ya. Iff'n you ain't be needin' them none, 'ow 'bout floatin' some my way...purty please?
        MY_OH_MY_OH_MY_THEM_OBSIDIAN_FRAGMENTS                                        = 12714,  -- My, oh my, oh my! Them obsidian fragments be twinklin' and gleamin' like spit-shined shoes. I think I sees my reflection in 'em!
        SORRY_I_M_EASILY_DISTRACTED_THESE_DAYS_WHERE                                  = 12715,  -- Sorry, I'm easily distracted these days. Where was I? Oh, yeah, did I ever tell ya how much I love buildin' simulacra?
        I_DID_HM_WELL_I_ALSO_LIKE_COLLECTIN                                           = 12716,  -- ...I did? Hm...well, I also like collectin' 'em.
        IFF_N_YOU_D_HAVE_A_HEART_BIGGER                                               = 12717,  -- Iff'n you'd have a heart bigger than the Celennia Memorial Library and give me one, I'd dun make it worth your while, that's fo' sho'.
        YA_CAN_AVE_SOME_SEGMENTS_FROM_MY_SUPER                                        = 12718,  -- Ya can 'ave some segments from my super-secret collection, so humor an ol' man and gimme, gimme, gimme!
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_LEAVE_CHECK_YOUR_SIMULACRUM                                  = 12719,  -- What will you do? Leave. Check your simulacrum. Dismantle a simulacrum. Check your eudaemon. Dismantle a eudaemon. Trade for segments from his collection.
        YA_WANT_ME_TO_HAVE_A_LOOK_SEE                                                 = 12720,  -- Ya want me to have a look-see at those [simulacrum/eudaemon] pieces o' yours? Great! But which ones?
        CHECK_WHICH_S_SEGMENTS_NONE                                                   = 12721,  -- Check which [simulacrum/eudaemon]'s segments? None. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %.
        WHAT_S_THAT_SONNY_MISSY_LESSEE                                                = 12722,  -- What's that, sonny/missy]? %? Lessee...
        ID_12723                                                                      = 12723,  -- %!
        DID_I_EAR_YA_SAY_DISMANTLE_I_GUESS                                            = 12724,  -- Did I 'ear ya say dismantle? I guess I cain't say They don't make 'em like they used to, because no one makes 'em anymore! Anyway, that's what these segments are for.
        DISMANTLE_WHICH_NONE                                                          = 12725,  -- Dismantle which [simulacrum/eudaemon]? None. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %.
        DISMANTLE_YOU_HEARD_ME_WHOOPS_NO_THANKS                                       = 12726,  -- Dismantle %? You heard me. Whoops! No, thanks.
        I_M_WILLIN_TO_DO_THIS_FOR_YA                                                  = 12727,  -- I'm willin' to do this for ya an' all, but what's the point iff'n I cain't give 'em back? You got stuff practic'ly cascadin' out your satchel!
        DO_DUM_DIDDLY_DAK_NOW_THAT_I_VE                                               = 12728,  -- Do dum diddly dak. Now that I've dismantled your simulacrum, 'ow many pieces d'ya get back?
        YOU_BROUGHT_SOME_OBSIDIAN_FRAGMENTS_FOR_ME_YA                                 = 12729,  -- You brought some obsidian fragments for me!? Ya shouldn't have...but I'm so glad ya did! Take anythin' ya want. Anythin' at all!
        SELECT_A_SEGMENT_FRAGMENT_NO_THANKS_NEEDED_NEEDED                             = 12730,  -- Select a segment. (# fragment[/s]) No, thanks. %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) Previous page. Next page.
        WHAT_A_BEAUT_THIS_YOU_LL_GIVE_ER                                              = 12731,  -- What a beaut, this %. You'll give 'er a good 'ome, won't ya?
        GIVE_A_GOOD_HOME_WITH_PLEASURE_I_D                                            = 12732,  -- Give % a good home? With pleasure. I'd rather not.
        JUST_BECAUSE_I_AIN_T_GOT_ALL_MY                                               = 12733,  -- Just because I ain't got all my marbles don't mean ya can try to stiff me on obsidian fragments! Lucky fer you I'll forget in a few minutes...
        SORRAH_NO_SUPER_SECRET_TREASURES_FROM_MY_COLLECTION                           = 12734,  -- Sorrah, no super secret treasures from my collection if ya cain't even find the time to empty your pack.
        WHOA_WHOA_WHOA_I_PPRECIATE_THE_GUSTO_BUT                                      = 12735,  -- Whoa, whoa, whoa! I 'ppreciate the gusto, but my mind just ain't the most agile. I need the three diff'rent pieces all at the same time...or four dependin' on the type. Didn't my wife tell ya that?
        LOOKS_LIKE_YA_CAUGHT_A_BIT_O_MY                                               = 12736,  -- Looks like ya caught a bit o' my senility, sonny/missy]. I think you've already got a [simulacrum/eudaemon] for this location.
        THERE_AIN_T_NO_NEED_FOR_MORE_N                                                = 12737,  -- There ain't no need for more'n one. I speak from experience, 'ere. Let's just pretend this ne'er 'appened.
        THIS_HEAD_THAT_TORSO_THESE_LEGS_I_THINK                                       = 12738,  -- This head, that torso, these legs... I think I'm gonna need # gil for this job.
        HAVE_HIM_ASSEMBLE_YES_NO                                                      = 12739,  -- Have him assemble %? Yes. No.
        HOLD_YOUR_CHOCOBOS_YOUNG_UN_YOU_CAIN_T                                        = 12740,  -- Hold your chocobos, young'un! You cain't rush genius!
        TWIST_ERE_PROD_THERE_GET_IN_THERE_DAMMIT                                      = 12741,  -- Twist 'ere, prod there... Get in there, dammit... Get the holy hell in there! Grrr...
        WHEW_FEAST_YOUR_PEEPERS_ON_THIS_HUMDINGER_AIN                                 = 12742,  -- Whew, feast your peepers on this humdinger! Ain't never seen somethin' so seamless, 'ave ya? And it's all yours, bairn.
        IF_YOUR_MEM_RY_S_A_BIT_FUZZY                                                  = 12743,  -- If your mem'ry's a bit fuzzy on what to do with these simulacra, go chat up my ol' lady for a bit. I wouldn't wanna spoil the surprise none.
        YA_DUN_FOUND_SOME_PROVERBIAL_DIAMONDS_IN_THE                                  = 12744,  -- Ya dun found some proverbial diamonds in the rough, didja?
        LEMME_TAKE_A_GANDER_AT_EM_HMMM_BY                                             = 12745,  -- Lemme take a gander at 'em. Hmmm... By golly, they should be fittin' tighter'n my ol' lady's britches after a Darksday brunch.
        BUT_OW_N_I_GO_BOUT_IT_BE                                                      = 12746,  -- But 'ow'n I go 'bout it be a differnt beast alt'gether. I guess I's just gots ta wing it.
        IF_YA_BE_WANTIN_ME_TO_WORK_MY                                                 = 12747,  -- If ya be wantin' me to work my magic, I'll needs me the visage, torso, legs, and...
        AND_WHATEVER_THAT_NEWFANGLED_THINGAMABOB_SEGMENT_BE_ALL                       = 12748,  -- ...And whatever that newfangled thingamabob segment be all at once. Ya 'ear me? All four at the same time, sonny/missy].
        I_KNOW_I_FANCY_MYSELF_A_TINKERER_BUT                                          = 12749,  -- I know I fancy myself a tinkerer, but I ain't no miracle worker! Ya just cain't assemble nothin' with this 'ere 'ead.
        YA_VE_HEARD_THE_WHOLE_SHEBANG_FROM_GRANNY                                     = 12750,  -- Ya've heard the whole shebang from Granny o'er there, yeah?
        COURSE_I_CAIN_T_REMEMBER_GOBSMACK_BOUT_NO                                     = 12751,  -- 'Course, I cain't remember gobsmack 'bout no demon.
        TH_ONLY_THANG_I_DONE_CAN_DO_IS                                                = 12752,  -- Th'only thang I done can do is r'member a gapin' hole in my mem'ry.
        WEREN_T_SO_MUCH_THAT_I_COULDN_T                                               = 12753,  -- Weren't so much that I couldn't set foot in skirmishes no more...
        MORE_THAT_I_FERGET_WHAT_TWAS_LIKE_TA                                          = 12754,  -- More that I ferget what 'twas like ta live.
        YER_SAYIN_THAT_OUR_UNBORN_DAUGHTER_WAS_TAK                                    = 12755,  -- Yer sayin' that our unborn daughter was tak'n from us and that she's alive in a skirmish?
        I_CAIN_T_EVEN_MAGINE_WHAT_THAT_MUS                                            = 12756,  -- I cain't even 'magine what that mus' be like for her...
        WHAT_GOOD_COULD_THESE_OLD_BONES_BE_TO                                         = 12757,  -- What good could these old bones be to one as spry as yourself?
        A_SIMULACRUM_YES_YOU_COULD_SAY_I_VE                                           = 12758,  -- A simulacrum...yes, you could say I've heard tales of such objects. This sap over here is a fan of collecting such dangerous articles.
        THEY_MAY_NOT_LOOK_SPECIAL_BUT_I_SWEAR                                         = 12759,  -- They may not look special, but I swear by all the gray hairs on this head that they contain latent hermetical energies.
        YES_AND_HARNESSING_SUCH_ENERGIES_GRANTS_THE_BEARER                            = 12760,  -- Yes...and harnessing such energies grants the bearer the ability to manipulate time and space itself.
        WOULD_YOU_THINK_ME_MAD_IF_I_TOLD                                              = 12761,  -- Would you think me mad if I told you that they were keys to another dimension?
        DO_YOU_BELIEVE_HER_STORY_ANYTHING_IS_POSSIBLE                                 = 12762,  -- Do you believe her story? Anything is possible. She's clearly off her rocker.
        IT_IS_GOOD_TO_SEE_THAT_NOT_ALL                                                = 12763,  -- It is good to see that not all youth have abandoned the realm of possibility.
        I_SUPPOSE_I_CANNOT_FAULT_YOU_FOR_DOUBTING                                     = 12764,  -- I suppose I cannot fault you for doubting, as my word is the only proof I offer.
        IT_IS_AS_I_SAID_BEFORE_THE_POWER                                              = 12765,  -- It is as I said before--the power is real. Find an augural conveyor, hold up the simulacrum, and watch the magic begin.
        WHAT_MAGIC_TOHOHO_FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME                                           = 12766,  -- What magic? Tohoho, far be it from me to spoil the fun!
        YOU_REMIND_ME_SO_MUCH_OF_MY_GRANDSON                                          = 12767,  -- You remind me so much of my grandson/granddaughter]. He/She] must be around your age, and always asking questions instead of going to find the answer for himself/herself]. But I say that there's no better teacher than experience.
        BUT_HEAVENS_HAVE_I_FINALLY_REACHED_THE_AGE                                    = 12768,  -- But heavens, have I finally reached the age when I've started to lecture youngsters? Let's nip that one in the bud.
        AS_I_WAS_SAYING_THE_SIMULACRA_PROVIDE_A                                       = 12769,  -- As I was saying, the simulacra provide a gateway to places known as skirmishes. Skirmishes look, smell, and sound exactly like Vana'diel.
        DON_T_GIVE_ME_THAT_LOOK_HOW_AM                                                = 12770,  -- Don't give me that look. How am I supposed to know why such a world exists? I'm just an old woman, not some learned sage! What I can tell you is that the simulacra are the key to entering a skirmish.
        WHEN_HE_AND_I_WERE_YOUNGER_WE_USED                                            = 12771,  -- When he and I were younger, we used to visit there the way those kids used to play hide-and-seek in the Rala Waterways.
        WE_HAD_ALL_MANNER_OF_INTERESTING_EXPERIENCES_THERE                            = 12772,  -- We had all manner of interesting experiences there--but I'm sure that's a story you've no interest in hearing.
        MAYBE_I_M_REPEATING_MYSELF_AGE_LL_DO                                          = 12773,  -- Maybe I'm repeating myself--age'll do that to you--but if you want to enter a skirmish, you must first find a lek of black butterflies.
        OF_COURSE_YOUNG_ONE_THIS_WAS_ALL_A                                            = 12774,  -- Of course, young one, this was all a long time ago. I don't even know if skirmishes continue to exist, or what form they may take today. All I ask is that you make careful preparations if you decide to visit such a dangerous area.
        OF_COURSE_I_WOULDN_T_FAULT_YOU_IF                                             = 12775,  -- Of course, I wouldn't fault you if you wanted to use the simulacrum as simply a lovely conversation piece to adorn your hearth.
        BUT_THAT_LOOK_IN_YOUR_EYES_I_CAN                                              = 12776,  -- But that look in your eyes--I can tell that you won't be satisfied until you try it out for yourself.
        GWEHEHE_THESE_RICKETY_BONES_FELT_THE_SAME_WHEN                                = 12777,  -- Gwehehe, these rickety bones felt the same when they were young.
        IF_YOU_EVER_WANT_TO_KNOW_MORE_ABOUT                                           = 12778,  -- If you ever want to know more about skirmishes, you know where to find me.
        HMM_IN_NEED_OF_SOME_OF_GRANNY_S                                               = 12779,  -- Hmm? In need of some of granny's musings?
        HAVE_ANY_QUESTIONS_NONE_IN_PARTICULAR_TELL_ME                                 = 12780,  -- Have any questions? None in particular. Tell me about skirmishes. Tell me how to access a skirmish. Tell me about the simulacra. Tell me about mysterious eddies. Tell me about skirmish prerequisites. Tell me about skirmish battles. Next page.
        I_WISH_I_COULD_TELL_YOU_WHY_SKIRMISHES                                        = 12781,  -- I wish I could tell you why skirmishes exist, or how long they've been there, but even the wisdom of an old woman has its limits. What I do know, though, is that physically speaking they're indistinguishable from our world.
        AUGURAL_CONVEYORS_SERVE_AS_GATEWAYS_TO_WHERE_SKIRMISHES                       = 12782,  -- Augural conveyors serve as gateways to where skirmishes take place. Find one, and you'll find your way there.
        TO_MAKE_YOUR_WAY_IN_YOU_LL_NEED                                               = 12783,  -- To make your way in, you'll need to hold up a simulacrum to the conveyor.
        DID_I_REMEMBER_TO_MENTION_THAT_EACH_ENTRANCE                                  = 12784,  -- Did I remember to mention that each entrance requires a different simulacrum? No?... <Sigh> They say you're only as old as you feel, but right now I feel like ancient ruins.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_IF_THERE_IS_SOME                                                 = 12785,  -- I don't know if there is some strange benefactor who controls the skirmishes, but the fact that % magically appears in your bag when you teleport there makes me think so. Using this object will enable you to return to our world. It's all very mysterious.
        THAT_WAY_EVEN_IF_YOU_RE_IN_OVER                                               = 12786,  -- That way, even if you're in over your head, you can still find your way out. Just don't go losing it, okay?
        LET_ME_SEE_IF_I_CAN_RECALL_ALL                                                = 12787,  -- Let me see if I can recall all the details... Yes, that's right. Here's what I can remember--but don't blame me if things have changed in the meantime!
        ONE_WAS_LOCATED_IN_RALA_WATERWAYS_IN_A                                        = 12788,  -- One was located in Rala Waterways, in a small cubbyhole to the west.
        ANOTHER_WAS_DEEP_WITHIN_THE_NORTHERNMOST_REGIONS_OF                           = 12789,  -- Another was deep within the northernmost regions of Cirdas Caverns.
        OH_YES_THAT_OLD_MAN_OF_MINE_JUST                                              = 12790,  -- Oh, yes, that old man of mine just loves his simulacra... Chiseling out their faces, collecting fresh herbs to grind into paint, and... Wait, what were we talking about?
        OH_RIGHT_SKIRMISHES_SORRY_ABOUT_THAT_FOR_SKIRMISHES                           = 12791,  -- Oh, right, skirmishes. Sorry about that. For skirmishes, the simulacra are divided up into three sections. The way you combine the segments determines what happens in the particular skirmish that you enter.
        THESE_THREE_PARTS_THE_VISAGE_THE_TORSO_THE                                    = 12792,  -- These three parts--the visage, the torso, the legs--each play a role in influencing the skirmish.
        OF_COURSE_I_DON_T_REMEMBER_WHICH_PART                                         = 12793,  -- Of course, I don't remember which part does what. Sometimes I'm lucky I remember to put on my blouse rightside-in each morning.
        I_DON_T_WANT_TO_SAY_THE_POSSIBILITIES                                         = 12794,  -- I don't want to say the possibilities are limitless...but there certainly are a lot of them, tohoho!
        IF_YOU_DO_DECIDE_TO_GO_AND_DISCOVER                                           = 12795,  -- If you do decide to go and discover anything interesting along the way, be sure to share your findings with gramps over there. He lives for this sort of thing.
        SWIRLING_POOLS_OF_POWER_KNOWN_AS_NOETIC_ASCENSIONS                            = 12796,  -- Swirling pools of power known as Noetic Ascensions dot the landscape of a skirmish.
        THE_NUMBER_OF_EDDIES_SEEMS_TO_VARY_WITH                                       = 12797,  -- The number of eddies seems to vary with...the combination of simulacrum segments? ...Prevailing weather patterns? ...Chocobo mating rituals?
        BAH_I_CAN_NEVER_KEEP_ALL_THIS_NONSENSE                                        = 12798,  -- Bah! I can never keep all this nonsense straight.
        DEAR_ME_I_VE_REALLY_STARTED_LOSING_IT                                         = 12799,  -- Dear me, I've really started losing it. What I can say for certain, though, is that you should take the time to harvest the eddies. They will help you somehow, I'm sure of it!
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_SEGMENT_OF_A_TRADE_THEM                                         = 12800,  -- Once you have # segment[/s] of a [simulacrum/eudaemon], trade them together to Oston, who will create a completed [simulacrum/eudaemon] for you in return.
        TO_ACCESS_A_SKIRMISH_THE_PARTY_LEADER_MUST                                    = 12801,  -- To access a skirmish, the party leader must be in possession of a [simulacrum/eudaemon] and find an augural conveyor.
        TALKING_TO_THE_AUGURAL_CONVEYOR_WILL_TRANSPORT_ALL                            = 12802,  -- Talking to the augural conveyor will transport all party members to this alternate realm of wonder.
        BACK_IN_THE_DAY_WE_D_TRY_TO                                                   = 12803,  -- Back in the day, we'd try to push it to the limits and once got as many as # people in a party! On the other hand, we were never able to go with fewer than #.
        ONLY_THOSE_OF_LEVEL_95_OR_HIGHER_ARE                                          = 12804,  -- Only those of level 95 or higher are granted access to [alluvion /]skirmishes.
        YOU_MAY_ONLY_SPEND_A_TOTAL_OF_BETWEEN                                         = 12805,  -- You may only spend a total of between # and # minute[/s] (Earth time) in [a skirmish/an alluvion skirmish] before being removed from the area. The amount of time changes depending on which combination of segments you have assembled.
        AFTER_THE_TIME_HAS_PASSED_YOU_WILL_BE                                         = 12806,  -- After the time has passed, you will be transported back to Vana'diel proper. A bit draconian, perhaps, but each simulacrum only holds so much power.
        IF_MINUTE_EARTH_TIME_PASS_WITHOUT_ANY_OF                                      = 12807,  -- If # minute[/s] (Earth time) pass[es/] without any of your companions residing inside the [alluvion /]skirmish, the realm will dematerialize.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_RETURN_TO_THIS_WORLD                                           = 12808,  -- If you wish to return to this world before the battle is done, you may use % to leave. All other party members will remain inside.
        HOWEVER_YOU_MAY_NOT_REENTER_ONCE_YOU_HAVE                                     = 12809,  -- However, you may not reenter [a skirmish/an alluvion skirmish] once you have left.
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_COMPLETE_THE_OBJECTIVES_YOU                                  = 12810,  -- If you manage to complete the objectives you will inevitably receive once inside, you will receive %.
        USING_THIS_WILL_OBLITERATE_ALL_REMAINING_FOES_AND                             = 12811,  -- Using this % will obliterate all remaining foes and conjure a treasure coffer. As yet another testament to the realm's strange nature, each participant will find their own rewards upon opening the coffer.
        IN_ADDITION_THE_AMOUNT_OF_TIME_REMAINING_BEFORE                               = 12812,  -- In addition, the amount of time remaining before you are teleported away will be reset to # minute[/s].
        MAKE_SURE_TO_CLAIM_YOUR_SPOILS_BEFORE_TIME                                    = 12813,  -- Make sure to claim your spoils before time expires.
        MIGHT_I_ADD_THAT_FULFILLING_ONE_CONDITION_WILL                                = 12814,  -- Might I add that fulfilling one condition will activate a second for you to attempt?
        COMPLETING_THIS_SECONDARY_OBJECTIVE_WILL_INCREASE_THE_REWARDS                 = 12815,  -- Completing this secondary objective will increase the rewards that you receive. Keep this in mind as you continue.
        OHOHO_MY_DEAR_HAVE_YOU_GOTTEN_HOLD_OF                                         = 12816,  -- Ohoho, my dear, have you gotten hold of one of the skirmishes' most precious items?
        YOU_KNOW_WHAT_I_MEAN                                                          = 12817,  -- You know what I mean--%.
        I_WENT_ON_SKIRMISHES_SO_MUCH_WHEN_I                                           = 12818,  -- I went on skirmishes so much when I was a bit more spry and these legs didn't turn to jelly just from climbing staircases, but never once did I get my hands on such a treasure. As for you, though...
        HMM_WITH_THAT_TERRIBLE_TRAVESTY_YOU_CALL_ARMOR                                = 12819,  -- Hmm...with that terrible travesty you call armor, even entering a skirmish must be a Starlight Celebration miracle.
        BUT_WHAT_A_TWINKLE_I_SEE_IN_YOUR                                              = 12820,  -- But what a twinkle I see in your eyes! Yes, you remind me of my younger days.
        YOU_THIRST_FOR_ADVENTURE_IN_FARAWAY_WORLDS                                    = 12821,  -- You thirst for adventure in faraway worlds.
        I_VE_STORED_THE_TRINKETS_I_VE_FOUND                                           = 12822,  -- I've stored the trinkets I've found over the years, hoping one day they would be put to good use--and maybe their time has come. Of course, sonny/dearie], all things have their price.
        AND_DON_T_THINK_I_LL_LET_YOU                                                  = 12823,  -- And don't think I'll let you steal all my hard-won trophies just because you have something shiny. You'll have to work for it, just as I did!
        YOU_MIGHT_LOOK_TOUGH_BUT_I_D_BET                                              = 12824,  -- You might look tough, but I'd bet every wrinkle on my body that there's even more fight inside of you. Come to think of it, that's a bet I wouldn't mind losing, tohoho!
        ANYWAY_TO_ACQUIRE_THEM_YOU_LL_NEED_TO                                         = 12825,  -- Anyway! To acquire them, you'll need to try your luck in some skirmishes.
        ONCE_YOU_VE_GOT_SOME_COME_BACK_HERE                                           = 12826,  -- Once you've got some, come back here and see me. I'll let you pick out something from my ancient collection.
        YOU_NEED_SOME_GUIDANCE_LET_GRANNY_LOLA_HELP                                   = 12827,  -- You need some guidance? Let Granny Lola help shine some of that old-time wisdom on you.
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_INFORMATION_ON_NOTHING_IN                                 = 12828,  -- What would you like information on? Nothing in particular. Skirmishes in general. Skirmish entrances. Simulacra. Noetic ascensions. %. I want to exchange %. I want my % returned. %. I want to exchange %. I want my % returned. Conditions for participating. Skirmish battles. Next page.
        THE_WINGS_IS_IT_YES_QUITE_MYSTERIOUS_ITEMS                                    = 12829,  -- The wings, is it? Yes, quite mysterious items, indeed.
        LET_ME_SHARE_WITH_YOU_SOME_INSIGHT_THOUGH                                     = 12830,  -- Let me share with you some insight: though one man's time on Vana'diel is limited, his curiosity stretches for eons.
        EVEN_I_ONCE_THOUGHT_THAT_CHASING_SOMETHING_SO                                 = 12831,  -- Even I once thought that chasing something so boundless was a fool's errand...but I was wrong.
        IN_MY_YOUNGER_DAYS_I_CHASED_AFTER_DREAMS                                      = 12832,  -- In my younger days, I chased after dreams like my crazy husband chased after women, yet I never stopped to think about why. Why I chased dreams, that is. I know why that letch chased women.
        THE_DEVIL_IS_IN_THE_DETAILS_THEY_SAY                                          = 12833,  -- The devil is in the details, they say, but I disagree. Don't worry about the little things--just enjoy the time you're given.
        GOODNESS_HAVE_I_GONE_ON_ABOUT_NOTHING_IN                                      = 12834,  -- Goodness, have I gone on about nothing in particular again? I really must stop doing that. What now? Beats me.
        WHAT_I_DO_KNOW_IS_THAT_EVERYTHING_SKIRMISH                                    = 12835,  -- What I do know is that everything skirmish creates has to do with those odd flitty thingamajigs.
        THE_ANSWERS_YOU_SEEK_MUST_LIE_WITHIN_THE                                      = 12836,  -- The answers you seek must lie within the skirmishes. Other than that, words fail me.
        LOOKING_TO_GET_HMM_TAKE_A_LOOK_AT                                             = 12837,  -- Looking to get [some of my armor/a bit of what I've got on me], hmm? Take a look at what I've got to offer.
        WHICH_ITEM_TOTAL_NONE_OF_THESE_NEEDED_NEEDED                                  = 12838,  -- Which item? (Total: #) None of these. %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) %. (# needed) Previous page. Next page.
        THIS_YOU_RE_ABSOLUTELY_SURE                                                   = 12839,  -- This %? You're absolutely sure?
        PROCEED_WITH_THE_EXCHANGE_WINGS_YES_NO                                        = 12840,  -- Proceed with the exchange? (Wings: #.) Yes. No.
        AND_I_THOUGHT_I_WAS_BAD_AT_ARITHMETIC                                         = 12841,  -- And I thought I was bad at arithmetic something fierce! You can't even remember how much stuff costs long enough to pay, can you? You'll need to get more % before I can give that to you!
        IS_THAT_I_SEE_HERE_LET_GRANNY_KEEP                                            = 12842,  -- Is that % I see? Here, let Granny keep ahold of any you got.
        I_M_HOLDING_A_TOTAL_OF_FOR_YOU                                                = 12843,  -- I'm holding a total of # for you. Just speak up when you want to exchange them for some of my [armor/stuff].
        TOHO_YOU_WANT_YOUR_BACK_AND_GRANNY_WAS                                        = 12844,  -- Toho, you want your % back? And Granny was keeping them nice and safe for you, too...
        I_M_HOLDING_A_TOTAL_OF_JUST_HOW                                               = 12845,  -- I'm holding a total of #. Just how many do I need to part with?
        UNDERSTOOD_YOUNG_CUB_THERE_YOU_GO                                             = 12846,  -- #? Understood, young cub. There you go.
        I_MIGHTN_T_GOT_A_HEAD_FOR_NUMBERS                                             = 12847,  -- I mightn't got a head for numbers, but returning zero means I keep all of them for you. Let me know if you change your mind.
        I_M_ONLY_HOLDING_FOR_YOU_BUT_YOU                                              = 12848,  -- I'm only holding # for you, but you want more? I may be old, but not that old!
        I_M_ALREADY_HOLDING_SUCH_A_HUGE_NUMBER                                        = 12849,  -- I'm already holding such a huge number that I can't possibly keep any more! Granny isn't your personal pack mule!
        YOUR_BAGS_ARE_FULL_SONNY_LASSIE_YOU_LL                                        = 12850,  -- Your bags are full, sonny/lassie]. You'll need to make some room first.
        THERE_S_YET_ANOTHER_DEEP_WITHIN_YORCIA_WEALD                                  = 12851,  -- There's yet another deep within Yorcia Weald. Beware the dense jungles if you decide to make the trek.
        TOHOHO_MY_YOUNG_FRIEND_YOU_VE_ALREADY_GOTTEN                                  = 12852,  -- Tohoho, my young friend. You've already gotten ahold of %!
        IT_BRINGS_ME_BACK_TO_A_TIME_WHEN                                              = 12853,  -- It brings me back to a time when my bosoms were a bit perkier and I, too, ventured across the land with a spring in my step...
        WITH_THOSE_TAUT_CALVES_OF_YOURS_YOU_MUST                                      = 12854,  -- With those taut calves of yours, you must surely be an adventurer just as capable as I used to be.
        IT_MAKES_ME_THINK_BACK_ON_OLD_TIMES                                           = 12855,  -- It makes me think back on old times with my compatriots. We were so young then...
        WITH_MY_GEOMANCY_AND_THE_OLD_GEEZER_S                                         = 12856,  -- With my geomancy and the old geezer's runes, not even the slimiest umbril stood in our way!
        BUT_SKIRMISHES_THOSE_WERE_ENTIRELY_DIFFERENT_CHALLENGES_INDEED                = 12857,  -- But skirmishes...those were entirely different challenges indeed.
        YET_MY_TRUSTY_LUOPAN_AND_THAT_FATTY_S                                         = 12858,  -- Yet my trusty luopan and that fatty's enchanted wards won the day, boy howdy!
        WE_DARTED_PAST_TRAPS_CLEAVED_DREAD_FOES_IN                                    = 12859,  -- We darted past traps, cleaved dread foes in two, and proceeded ever further into the otherworldly realm.
        SAY_IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_TRY_YOUR_HAND                                            = 12860,  -- Say...if you happen to try your hand at more skirmishes, would you bring an old woman some %?
        I_WOULD_TELL_YOU_THAT_RESPECTING_YOUR_ELDERS                                  = 12861,  -- I would tell you that respecting your elders' wishes would be reward enough, but, if you're anything like I used to be, I know you'll be wanting more.
        ALLOW_ME_TO_SWEETEN_THE_POT_IN_EXCHANGE                                       = 12862,  -- Allow me to sweeten the pot--in exchange for those mementos, I will happily part with a little something I used on my own jaunts into the ether.
        TOHOHO_I_PROMISE_THAT_THEY_VE_BEEN_STORED                                     = 12863,  -- Tohoho, I promise that they've been stored properly, so you won't have to worry that pretty little head of yours about fifty years of sweat and mildew!
        TOHOHO_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_WHY_GRANNY_IS                                         = 12864,  -- Tohoho, you wish to know why Granny is interested in such trinkets?
        THIS_LL_BE_A_BIT_RAMBLY_BUT_LET                                               = 12865,  -- This'll be a bit rambly, but let me tell you a story. A story of love and betrayal. A story of victory and defeat. A story...of Lola.
        I_HAVE_BEEN_THROUGH_MANY_SKIRMISHES_SOME_VEXING                               = 12866,  -- I have been through many skirmishes--some vexing, but all of them brutal. The foes were always numerous, and we were under assault from all sides.
        MY_LEGS_BEGAN_TO_BUCKLE_AND_I_FEARED                                          = 12867,  -- My legs began to buckle, and I feared I'd never again taste the sweet, succulent apples grown in the Civic Arboretum.
        WHEN_CLAWS_WERE_ABOUT_TO_REND_ME_LIMB                                         = 12868,  -- When claws were about to rend me limb from limb, I flinched, twisting to the side--and my bag full of % absorbed what would surely have been the killing blow.
        I_SWEAR_UPON_ALL_THAT_IS_HOLY_THAT                                            = 12869,  -- I swear upon all that is holy that my heart stopped for a good ten seconds. My comrades let out a cry of joy when they saw I was unscathed.
        BUT_GRAMPS_HE_WAS_NOT_SO_LUCKY_A                                              = 12870,  -- But Gramps--he was not so lucky. A fierce slash cut right above his kneecap, and he still bears that scar to this day--all because he didn't have %.
        I_FELT_SO_BAD_FOR_HIM_VENTURING_INTO                                          = 12871,  -- I felt so bad for him. Venturing into further skirmishes with such a grievous wound was out of the question, but I never wanted to leave his side--so I married the old coot.
        AND_ON_THE_NIGHT_OF_OUR_HONEYMOON_WE                                          = 12872,  -- And on the night of our honeymoon, we... Well, let's just say Granny used to be quite limber.
        TOHO_I_TOLD_YOU_THE_STORY_WOULD_BE                                            = 12873,  -- Toho, I told you the story would be a doozy!
        MAYBE_NOW_YOU_SEE_WHY_I_WANT_SOME                                             = 12874,  -- Maybe now you see why I want some of those things. They are wonderful memories of the best years of my life.
        NOW_YOU_UNDERSTAND_WHY_I_AM_WILLING_TO                                        = 12875,  -- Now you understand why I am willing to part with my trinkets for what, at the surface, are worthless pieces of junk.
        IF_I_RECALL_THERE_S_YET_ANOTHER_IN                                            = 12876,  -- If I recall, there's yet another in Ra'Kaznar, in a room near the upper level entrance.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHICH_TOTAL_ON_SECOND_THOUGHT_NOTHING                            = 12877,  -- Exchange for which? (Total: #). On second thought, nothing. Key items. Items.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHICH_TOTAL_I_VE_CHANGED_MY                                      = 12878,  -- Exchange for which? (Total: #) I've changed my mind. % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). % (# needed). Previous page. Next page.
        SONNY_LASSIE_GOOD_CHOICE                                                      = 12879,  -- %, sonny/lassie]? Good choice.
        AS_A_SPECIAL_BONUS_I_LL_TRADE_YOU                                             = 12880,  -- As a special bonus, I'll trade you % for a total of # wings, and % for a total of # wings.
        YOUNG_UN_WHERE_D_YOU_GET_YOUR_HANDS                                           = 12881,  -- Young'un, where'd you get your hands on that?
        IT_S_ANOTHER_ONE_OF_THOSE_SEGMENTS_ISN                                        = 12882,  -- It's another one of those segments, isn't it?
        A_BIT_DIFFERENT_FROM_THE_NORMAL_SIMULACRA_TO                                  = 12883,  -- A bit different from the normal simulacra, to be sure...but I feel the same faint energies.
        I_M_SURE_OLD_GRAMPS_OVER_THERE_D                                              = 12884,  -- I'm sure old gramps over there'd love to have a look at it.
        YOU_KNOW_HIM_HE_CAN_CREATE_SOMETHING_OUTTA                                    = 12885,  -- You know him--he can create something outta nothing!
        SEE_I_M_NOT_ANY_OLD_WEATHERED_CRONE                                           = 12886,  -- See? I'm not any old weathered crone, despite the way you rolled your eyes at me earlier.
        I_D_LIKE_TO_CALL_THEM_A_NEW                                                   = 12887,  -- I'd like to call them a new kind of simulacrum, but isn't that name a bit tiresome?
        I_VE_GOT_TO_COME_UP_WITH_SOMETHING                                            = 12888,  -- I've got to come up with something better... Why don't we call it a eudaemon?
        AND_THE_SKIRMISHES_THEY_RE_ATTUNED_TO_NEED                                    = 12889,  -- And the skirmishes they're attuned to need a moniker that'll just knock your socks off! Let's see...
        ID_12890                                                                      = 12890,  -- ...
        HMM_YOU_THINK_I_WOULD_GO_AND_PASS                                             = 12891,  -- Hmm? You think I would go and pass out like that, right here at this table? Granny may be past her prime, but she's not one to nod off in the middle of a conversation!
        HMM_HMMMMMM                                                                   = 12892,  -- Hmm... Hmmmmmm...
        I_VE_GOT_IT_WE_LL_CALL_THEM                                                   = 12893,  -- I've got it! We'll call them alluvion skirmishes!
        TOHOHO_MY_BRAIN_CAN_KEEP_UP_WHERE_MY                                          = 12894,  -- Tohoho, My brain can keep up where my body can't, that's for sure!
        AND_SINCE_YOU_VE_GOT_ONE_OF_THOSE                                             = 12895,  -- And since you've got one of those eudaemons, I've got a special task for you.
        YOU_MIGHT_FIND_A_PERNICIOUS_FIEND_ON_THE                                      = 12896,  -- You might find a pernicious fiend on the other side of those living cairns.
        IF_YOU_SEE_HIM_ASK_HIM_WHAT_THE                                               = 12897,  -- If you see him, ask him what the future holds.
        MY_OWN_FUTURE_MAY_BE_A_BIT_SHORTER                                            = 12898,  -- My own future may be a bit shorter than I'd care to admit, yet I can't help but be a bit curious.
        SO_YOU_LEARNED_NOTHING                                                        = 12899,  -- So you learned...nothing.
        BUT_YOU_DID_MANAGE_TO_MEET_HIM_AND                                            = 12900,  -- But you did manage to meet him, and it makes me wonder...
        JUST_WHAT_LIES_BEYOND_I_VE_SEARCHED_FOR                                       = 12901,  -- Just what lies beyond? I've searched for dozens of years, and these wrinkly old fingers have never grasped the answer.
        HOW_CAN_GRANNY_HELP_YOU_TODAY_I_REQUIRE                                       = 12902,  -- How can granny help you today? I require nothing. Tell me about alluvion skirmishes. Tell me how to join alluvion skirmishes. Tell me about eudaemon. Tell me about alluvion prerequisites. Tell me about alluvion battles. Previous page.
        WELL_THESE_OLD_BONES_RE_PRETTY_SURE_THEY                                      = 12903,  -- Well, these old bones're pretty sure they're similar to ordinary skirmishes, but I've never set foot inside the alluvion ones.
        AND_IF_THEY_RE_TRULY_LIKE_COUSINS_THEN                                        = 12904,  -- And if they're truly like cousins, then you'd need to find an augural conveyor to get in. Simple, right?
        DON_T_EXPECT_TO_JUST_TOUCH_THOSE_BUTTERFLIES                                  = 12905,  -- Don't expect to just touch those butterflies and be magically whisked away. You'll need a eudaemon to enter.
        REMEMBER_HOW_YOU_NEEDED_PARTS_CORRESPONDING_TO_A                              = 12906,  -- Remember how you needed parts corresponding to a particular area for an ordinary skirmish? Well, call it an old woman's intuition, but I'll bet eudaemons are similar.
        MAYBE_YOU_RE_STILL_SPRIGHTLY_AND_FULL_OF                                      = 12907,  -- Maybe you're still sprightly and full of life, but don't expect to waltz into a skirmish without the right eudaemon!
