        PART_WITH_THE_EQUIPMENT_YES_NO                                                = 13353,  -- Part with the equipment? Yes. No.
        MY_APOLOGIES_I_WAS_UNAWARE_THAT_YOU_SIMPLY                                    = 13354,  -- My apologies, %. I was unaware that you simply wanted to flaunt in front of another rune fencer.
        THANK_YOU_SNIFF_I_HOPE_MY_TEARS_OF                                            = 13355,  -- Thank you! <Sniff> I hope my tears of gratitude have an outlet to the Senroh Sea lest they cause a flood. Oh, and do not hesitate to provide more equipment if you have any.
        THE_NEXT_TIME_YOU_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON                                           = 13356,  -- The next time you get your hands on some, please hand them over to me!
        THAT_LOOKS_POSITIVELY_SPLENDID_ON_YOU_MAY_IT                                  = 13357,  -- That % looks positively splendid on you, %. May it serve you well in battle.
        YOUR_PATH_HAS_BEEN_LONG_AND_HARD_JUST                                         = 13358,  -- Your path has been long and hard, just as I warned you so long ago that it would be. Yet, look how far you have come in spite of it all.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_HAVE_SOARED_TO_THE_HEIGHTS                                       = 13359,  -- Now that you have soared to the heights I predicted you would, it is time for you to embark on your final test.
        OR_IT_WOULD_BE_IF_THERE_WAS_NOT                                               = 13360,  -- ...Or it would be if there was not a certain setback set before us.
        WE_HAVE_NOT_HELD_THE_ULTIMATE_TRIAL_FOR                                       = 13361,  -- We have not held the ultimate trial for rune fencers ever since that fateful accident two years ago.
        AS_YOU_CAN_IMAGINE_I_HAVE_A_FAVOR                                             = 13362,  -- As you can imagine, I have a favor to ask of you regarding this.
        I_AM_FULLY_AWARE_OF_MY_IMPERTINENCE_BUT                                       = 13363,  -- I am fully aware of my impertinence, but this requires skill that only someone of your caliber and experience possesses.
        WOULD_YOU_PLEASE_GET_TO_THE_BOTTOM_OF                                         = 13364,  -- Would you please get to the bottom of why the trial went bottom-up?
        TAKE_ON_THE_TASK_IT_WOULD_BE_MY                                               = 13365,  -- Take on the task? It would be my pleasure. No, do your own work.
        YOUR_REPLY_IS_A_CAUSTIC_VERBAL_VENOM_I                                        = 13366,  -- Your reply is a caustic verbal venom I completely expected, yet I have no retort for it. I cannot argue with infallible logic, so will instead fall back on apology. Please forgive my brashness.
        AT_THE_RISK_OF_SEEMING_INCOMPETENT_I_ASK                                      = 13367,  -- At the risk of seeming incompetent, I ask you to kindly reconsider your decision on looking into the final trial.
        THANK_YOU_EVER_SO_MUCH_I_HOPE_THAT                                            = 13368,  -- Thank you ever so much. I hope that, one of these days, I can salvage what little remains of your shipwrecked image of me.
        BEFORE_YOU_BEGIN_YOUR_FACT_FINDING_MISSION_HOWEVER                            = 13369,  -- Before you begin your fact-finding mission, however, I must impart upon you this object of apodictic import.
        IT_IS_A_PICTURESQUE_DEVICE_THAT_CAN_BOTH                                      = 13370,  -- It is %, a picturesque device that can both record pictures on and project them from rune stones.
        THIS_IS_THE_SAME_TYPE_OF_CONTRAPTION_A                                        = 13371,  -- This is the same type of contraption a researcher from the Inventors' Coalition used to record the events of that trial two years prior.
        BY_ALL_ACCOUNTS_IT_WAS_STILL_ACCOUNTED_FOR                                    = 13372,  -- By all accounts, it was still accounted for somewhere in the Inventors' Coalition. I need you to review their footage and judge whether or not the current trial is appropriate for rune fencers to undertake.
        SPEAK_TO_GADDIUX_WHO_HAS_BEEN_INSTRUCTED_TO                                   = 13373,  -- Speak to Gaddiux, who has been instructed to divulge all the necessary information.
        SIMPLY_INQUIRE_ABOUT_HE_WILL_UNDERSTAND_WHAT_YOU                              = 13374,  -- Simply inquire about %. He will understand what you mean.
        OH_HAVE_THE_WINDS_OF_UNDERSTANDING_BLOWN_YOU                                  = 13375,  -- Oh, %. Have the winds of understanding blown you here with a gust of new information?
        I_SEE_IT_CERTAINLY_LOOKS_AS_IF_THE                                            = 13376,  -- I see... It certainly looks as if the visual record contained in that rock has rocked your image of the trial.
        WOULD_YOU_MIND_APPRISING_ME_OF_YOUR_DISCOVERY                                 = 13377,  -- Would you mind apprising me of your discovery?
        WHAT_DID_YOU_DISCOVER_SOMEONE_WENT_MISSING_THERE                              = 13378,  -- What did you discover? Someone went missing. There's a monster in %.
        IT_IS_AS_YOU_SAY_A_RESEARCHER_DID                                             = 13379,  -- It is as you say. A researcher did indeed go missing after the incident.
        HER_NAME_WAS_MIKOLULU_AND_SHE_WAS_ACCOMPANYING                                = 13380,  -- Her name was Mikolulu...and she was accompanying her younger brother on the ultimate trial.
        THE_ONLY_CLUES_TO_HER_WHEREABOUTS_WE_COULD                                    = 13381,  -- The only clues to her whereabouts we could obtain were the severed tip of her broadsword and patches of chainmail.
        I_FEAR_THAT_SHE_GULP_EVEN_NOW_THOSE                                           = 13382,  -- I fear that she... <Gulp> Even now, those words are too painful to speak aloud.
        NOT_EVEN_THE_MOST_CLANDESTINE_OF_FACTS_ESCAPES                                = 13383,  -- Not even the most clandestine of facts escapes you.
        THOUGH_I_HAVE_NEVER_FORAYED_INTO_I_COULD                                      = 13384,  -- Though I have never forayed into %, I could never forget about the abomination that fouls the waters there.
        MANY_OF_THE_SURVEYORS_WHO_VENTURED_INTO_THE                                   = 13385,  -- Many of the surveyors who ventured into the Ulbukan jungle were devoured by it. The beast gained such an abhorrent reputation that soon it became known as Insidio.
        THE_CITY_ASSEMBLED_A_BAND_OF_ITS_FINEST                                       = 13386,  -- The city assembled a band of its finest warriors to dispatch Insidio, and they returned seemingly victorious. However, it quickly returned as if nothing had ever transpired. Perhaps it only left to spawn or somesuch and our extermination plan never truly succeeded at all.
        IT_IS_NOT_A_FAR_FETCHED_ASSUMPTION_TO                                         = 13387,  -- It is not a far-fetched assumption to make, considering the cunning Insidio displays in battle. Its most fearsome trick is to turn opponents' allies into enemies by manipulating their minds.
        WHILE_I_WOULD_RATHER_AVOID_ENTANGLING_YOU_IN                                  = 13388,  -- While I would rather avoid entangling you in this affair, my hands are tied at the moment and I am left with no other recourse.
        WOULD_YOU_PLEASE_MAKE_FOR_AND_RID_IT                                          = 13389,  -- Would you please make for % and rid it of Insidio? Do this for the good of the city, for the colonization initiative...
        AND_FOR_ME_I_HAVE_LOST_SCORES_OF                                              = 13390,  -- And for me. I have lost scores of friends and fellow countrymen to that fish's lure and wish to see someone finally reel in that atrocity once and for all.
        OH_OH_MY_THAT_IS_IS_IT_NOT                                                    = 13391,  -- Oh...oh my! That is...%, is it not!?
        THE_FINITE_NATURE_OF_OUR_LANGUAGE_DEFINITELY_DOES                             = 13392,  -- The finite nature of our language definitely does not allow me to adequately express the extent of my gratitude, but I hope the following will suffice.
        ON_BEHALF_OF_INSIDIO_S_VICTIMS_AND_ALL                                        = 13393,  -- On behalf of Insidio's victims and all those who have suffered in its wake, thank you.
        YOU_HAVE_PROVED_A_TREMENDOUS_HELP_IN_REGARDS                                  = 13394,  -- You have proved a tremendous help in regards to the ultimate trial as well.
        IS_THERE_ANYTHING_YOU_WOULD_LIKE_TO_SAY                                       = 13395,  -- Is there anything you would like to say about it?
        WHAT_ABOUT_THE_ULTIMATE_TRIAL_THE_AREA_S                                      = 13396,  -- What about the ultimate trial? The area's too dangerous. It needs more hints. Make clear what the rewards are. Prioritize safety. It lacks impact. Where's the love? It's completely useless. I have nothing to say.
        AS_A_MEMBER_OF_THE_ORDER_OF_ORVAIL                                            = 13397,  -- As a member of the Order of Orvail, it would pain me to see your advice come to no avail, but I do not foresee the trial going away anytime soon. Your opinion, however, is much appreciated.
        YOUR_WORDS_GIVE_ME_WINGS_THANK_YOU_FOR                                        = 13398,  -- Your words give me wings. Thank you for the vote of confidence. ...Or is this a case of If you have nothing nice to say, say nothing at all?
        HMMM_YOUR_CRITICISM_CERTAINLY_HAS_MERIT_I_PROMISE                             = 13399,  -- Hmmm...your criticism certainly has merit. I promise to take it into consideration when revising this most critical of trials.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_HAVE_METAPHORICALLY_SCRATCHED_MY_BACK                            = 13400,  -- Now that you have metaphorically scratched my back, it is time that I scratched yours.
        HERE_IT_IS_GIVEN_TO_RUNE_FENCERS_WHO                                          = 13401,  -- Here it is, %...given to rune fencers who have gone above and beyond the call of duty.
        THIS_PARTICULAR_PIECE_OF_EQUIPMENT_WAS_WOVEN_BY                               = 13402,  -- This particular piece of equipment was woven by the most polished artisan known to Ulbuka, so wear it with pride.
        I_WONDER_HOW_THAT_TARUTARU_S_FACE_WOULD                                       = 13403,  -- I wonder how that Tarutaru's face would look if he had completed the trial two years ago and I was able to give him this as I just have to you...
        TO_YOU_WHO_HAVE_TRANSCENDED_THE_RANKS_OF                                      = 13404,  -- To you, who have transcended the ranks of common rune fencers and amassed vaults of memories along the way, may your smile always beam with the power of the runes and your blade cut the air with the precision of the most proficient calligrapher.
        I_WAS_REMISS_TO_MENTION_THAT_WE_KNOW                                          = 13405,  -- I was remiss to mention that we know not how to replenish the energies that power % once they are depleted.
        DO_AWAY_WITH_IT_HOW_YOU_WISH                                                  = 13406,  -- Do away with it how you wish.
        YOUR_FATE_RIDES_ON_THE_CHANGING_WINDS_OF                                      = 13407,  -- Your fate rides on the changing winds of Vana'diel. I can give you insight on the local weather.
        WHAT_AREA_S_WEATHER_DO_YOU_WISH_TO                                            = 13408,  -- What area's weather do you wish to know? Nowhere. Ronfaure. La Theine Plateau. Valkurm Dunes. Jugner Forest. Batallia Downs. Gustaberg. Konschtat Highlands. Pashhow Marshlands. Rolanberry Fields. Beaucedine Glacier. Xarcabard. Cape Teriggan. Altepa Desert. Sarutabaruta. Tahrongi Canyon. Buburimu Peninsula. Meriphataud Mountains. Sauromugue Champaign. The Sanctuary of Zi'Tah. Yuhtunga & Yhoator Jungles. Qufim Island. Tu'Lia. Ferry. Airship. Jeuno. Uleguerand Range. Tavnazian Archipelago. Riverne - Sites #A01 & #B01.
        THAT_AREA_S_FORECAST_FOR_TODAY_IS_FOR                                         = 13409,  -- That area's forecast for today is for % with occasional %. There is also a slight chance of %, so caution is advised.
        THE_FORECAST_FOR_TOMORROW_IS_FOR_WITH_OCCASIONAL                              = 13410,  -- The forecast for tomorrow is for % with occasional %. There is also a slight chance of %, so caution is advised.
