        RESETTING_REWARDS_WILL_INCREASE_THE_NUMBER_OF_DEEDS                           = 13526,  -- Resetting rewards will increase the number of deeds required but will let you reobtain items you have previously received.
        YOU_ARE_ABLE_TO_RESET_YOUR_REWARDS_FOR                                        = 13527,  -- You are able to reset your rewards for # deed[/s].
        RESET_REWARDS_YES_RESET_NO                                                    = 13528,  -- Reset rewards? Yes. (Reset ##) No.
        YOU_HAVE_NOT_YET_RECEIVED_SOME_REWARDS_RESETTING                              = 13529,  -- You have not yet received some rewards. Resetting means that you will be unable to obtain them. Are you sure?
        REALLY_RESET_REWARDS_YES_RESET_NO                                             = 13530,  -- Really reset rewards? Yes. (Reset ##) No.
        REWARDS_HAVE_BEEN_RESET                                                       = 13531,  -- Rewards have been reset.
        WELCOME_HOME_LADY_INGRID                                                      = 13532,  -- Welcome home, Lady Ingrid.
        A_MOMENT_FOOL                                                                 = 13533,  -- [Adventurer,/You there,] a moment, fool.
        I_HAVE_BEEN_APPRISED_OF_THE_JEUNO_INSTITUTE                                   = 13534,  -- I have been apprised of the Jeuno Institute of Magical Studies' new Trust initiative. You are enrolled in this abomination too, as I understand it.
        CAN_YOU_USE_TRUST_MAGIC_SURE_CAN_UH                                           = 13535,  -- Can you use Trust magic? Sure can. Uh...no?
        MY_INSTINCTS_ARE_NEVER_WRONG_IT_S_A                                           = 13536,  -- My instincts are never wrong. It's a blessing from Altana herself.
        YOUR_TONGUE_IS_AS_BLACK_AS_THE_UMBRILS                                        = 13537,  -- Your tongue is as black as the umbrils that blight this land.
        AS_AN_EXORCIST_OF_THE_HIGHEST_CALIBER_RECOGNIZING                             = 13538,  -- As an exorcist of the highest caliber, recognizing those whose talents may be of use comes as second nature.
        YOU_ARE_CERTAINLY_AWARE_OF_HOW_I_VISITED                                      = 13539,  -- You are certainly aware of how I visited the Middle Lands for a time. Even the most reclusive shut-in knows that.
        MY_TRAVELS_TOOK_ME_TO_THE_INSTITUTE_WHERE                                     = 13540,  -- My travels took me to the institute, where they correctly asked me to be a participant in the initiative.
        ALL_ADOULIN_EXPECTS_ME_TO_SERVE_AS_THEIR                                      = 13541,  -- All Adoulin expects me to serve as their face in a foreign land. It would be uncouth of me to refuse such an opportunity.
        FURTHER_IMAGINE_HOW_WELL_IT_WOULD_REFLECT_ON                                  = 13542,  -- Further, imagine how well it would reflect on Vortimere if we were to discover how...
        BUT_LAYING_THAT_ASIDE_FOR_NOW                                                 = 13543,  -- But laying that aside for now...
        CONSIDER_YOURSELF_TOUCHED_BY_FATE_THAT_I_DEIGN                                = 13544,  -- [My excellence is beyond parallel in this land, Middle Lander./You have witnessed firsthand the unsurpassed power that I wield.] Consider yourself touched by fate that I deign to participate in the ritual with you.
        JOURNEY_WITH_INGRID_HOW_COULD_I_NOT_WHY                                       = 13545,  -- Journey with Ingrid? How could I not? Why on earth would I?
        HOW_COULD_YOU_DENY_ME_AFTER_EVERYTHING_YOU                                    = 13546,  -- How could you deny me, after everything you have seen!?
        A_GRAVE_MISTAKE_AND_ONE_THAT_COULD_ONLY                                       = 13547,  -- A grave mistake, and one that could only be made by someone unfamiliar with my true power.
        PERFECT_LET_THE_MERCILESS_ONE_GUIDE_YOU                                       = 13548,  -- Perfect! Let the Merciless One guide you!
        TRUE_TO_ITS_NAME_THE_RITUAL_REQUIRES_TRUST                                    = 13549,  -- True to its name, the ritual requires trust between two individuals. Let us reflect...
        YOUR_BRASH_INSOLENCE_WAS_EVIDENT_FROM_THE_FIRST                               = 13550,  -- Your brash insolence was evident from the first time you opened your mouth.
        BUT_MY_STRENGTH_OF_SPIRIT_SHALL_SEE_US                                        = 13551,  -- But my strength of spirit shall see us through, nonetheless.
        YES_I_SUPPOSE_I_DO_TRUST_YOU_DESPITE                                          = 13552,  -- Yes, I suppose I do trust you. Despite everything, you came to me during my time of need.
        YOUR_STRONG_WILL_SHALL_SURELY_SEE_US_THROUGH                                  = 13553,  -- Your strong will shall surely see us through.
        LET_US_PROCEED                                                                = 13554,  -- Let us proceed.
        MERCILESS_INDEED_THE_REST_I_LEAVE_UP_TO                                       = 13555,  -- Merciless, indeed! The rest I leave up to you.
        WHY_CAN_YOU_NOT_SAY_WHAT_YOU_FEEL                                             = 13556,  -- Why can you not say what you feel?
        WHAT_I_FEEL                                                                   = 13557,  -- What I...feel?
        YOU_WISH_TO_THANK_FOR_ALL_HE_SHE                                              = 13558,  -- You wish to thank % for all he/she] has done for you. Why must you hold back?
        DARE_YOU_FORGET_WHICH_ONE_OF_US_IS                                            = 13559,  -- Dare you forget which one of us is the mistress?! I--
        YOU_HIDE_BEHIND_A_PRICKLY_MASK_BUT_WE                                         = 13560,  -- You hide behind a prickly mask, but we both know your inner voice speaks of him/her] as softly as freshly washed velvet.
        S_SILENCE_WE_VE_FINISHED_THE_RITUAL_SO                                        = 13561,  -- S-silence! We've finished the ritual, so I hereby banish you to the aether!
        HMPH_5                                                                        = 13562,  -- Hmph.
        DESPITE_YOUR_GREATEST_EFFORTS_TO_DERAIL_THIS_RITUAL                           = 13563,  -- Despite your greatest efforts to derail this ritual, it appears to have been a success. My alter ego shall surely be of great use to you.
        WITH_ADOULIN_S_MOST_PROMINENT_EXORCIST_AT_YOUR                                = 13564,  -- With Adoulin's most prominent exorcist at your side, your foes will tremble and flee!
        YES_THIS_INCANTATION_ONLY_STRENGTHENS_MY_ABILITY_TO                           = 13565,  -- Yes... This incantation only strengthens my ability to purge the world of its ills. Let it take wing and guide you...
        ONLY_ONCE_THE_WORLD_IS_CLEAN_WILL_I                                           = 13566,  -- Only once the world is clean will I finally be free of this pain.
        MOMMY_I                                                                       = 13567,  -- Mommy, I...
        I_MUST_REQUEST_THAT_YOU_INQUIRE_ANOTHER_TIME                                  = 13568,  -- I must request that you inquire another time, as the order is inundated with various issues these past few moons.
        THINGS_KEEP_TURNING_FROM_BAD_TO_WORSE                                         = 13569,  -- Things keep turning from bad to worse.
        AND_LOOK_WHO_S_COME_TO_SPRINKLE_ROCK                                          = 13570,  -- And look who's come to sprinkle rock salt in my wounds. <Sigh> As long as you insist on bringing thunderclouds into my life, I might as well ask--you're familiar with Hildebert, yes?
        DO_YOU_REMEMBER_HILDEBERT_HILDEWHO_OH_YEAH_THE                                = 13571,  -- Do you remember Hildebert? Hildewho? Oh, yeah, the old guy. Say nothing.
        THE_HEAD_OF_THE_ORDER_OF_WEATHERSPOON_ALWAYS                                  = 13572,  -- The head of the Order of Weatherspoon, always wearing those same tired white vestments.
        UGH_I_M_EMINENTLY_AWARE_THAT_NOT_ALL                                          = 13573,  -- Ugh. I'm eminently aware that not all of us have a way with names, but if you're going to barge into the castle and stick your fingers in everyone's pies, you should at least have the decency to answer a simple question!
        WELL_NOW_YOU_VE_DISCOVERED_A_CHARACTER_FLAW                                   = 13574,  -- Well, now you've discovered a character flaw to work on. One of many, I presume.
        YOU_ARE_AWARE_THAT_HIS_WIFE_FELL_ILL                                          = 13575,  -- [Then perhaps/I would perhaps be wrong to presume that] you are aware that his wife fell ill due to some strange demon called Balamor's machinations?
        WERE_YOU_AWARE_OF_THIS_FACT_O_OF                                              = 13576,  -- Were you aware of this fact? O-of course! Nope.
        OHO_THEN_I_M_SURE_YOU_CAN_ALSO                                                = 13577,  -- Oho. Then I'm sure you can also tell me what her name is.
        NATURALLY_EVEN_THE_MOST_LOOSE_LIPPED_AMONG_OUR                                = 13578,  -- Naturally. Even the most loose-lipped among our order knows better than to start spreading that around.
        FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME_TO_SYMPATHIZE_WITH                                          = 13579,  -- Far be it from me to sympathize with Hildebert--or anyone, really--when he's fighting with our beloved princess, but even I must confess to harboring a bit of pity for his son, Marcellurin.
        THE_BLOOD_OF_GENERATIONS_OF_EXORCISTS_COURSES_THROUGH                         = 13580,  -- The blood of generations of exorcists courses through her veins, and she is more susceptible than most to the whims and whimsies of spirits.
        SHE_DID_RETURN_TO_US_FOR_A_BRIEF                                              = 13581,  -- She did return to us for a brief while when you purged Hades from the land...
        BUT_THE_SLUMBER_HAS_TAKEN_HOLD_OF_HER                                         = 13582,  -- ...But the slumber has taken hold of her once more. The sun has thrice risen since her eyes opened last. Even I must confess concern, not only for her, but for her son, Marcellurin.
        INGRID_YOU_NEED_NOT_MISS_ANY_SLEEP_OVER                                       = 13583,  -- Ingrid, you need not miss any sleep over my mental state.
        MY_DUTY_IS_TO_SUPPORT_BOTH_MY_FATHER                                          = 13584,  -- My duty is to support both my father and the Order of Weatherspoon during times of crisis.
        ALTANA_KNOWS_THAT_NO_LOVE_HAS_BEEN_LOST                                       = 13585,  -- Altana knows that no love has been lost between you and my father over these past few months.
        AND_DESPITE_THE_PAST_YOU_HAVE_SPENT_COUNTLESS                                 = 13586,  -- And despite the past, you have spent countless nights working with Arciela for the betterment of us all.
        AH_THE_RAMBLINGS_OF_A_MADMAN_NEVER_CEASE                                      = 13587,  -- Ah, the ramblings of a madman never cease, do they?
        YET_DO_NOT_THINK_ME_WHOLLY_WITHOUT_HEART                                      = 13588,  -- Yet do not think me wholly without heart. I take full responsibility for the chaos within the order.
        I_HAD_HOPED_TO_SEEK_HIS_COUNSEL_BUT                                           = 13589,  -- I had hoped to seek his counsel...but my tongue always gets the better of me.
        THE_CURSE_HAS_TAKEN_ITS_TOLL_ON_MANY                                          = 13590,  -- The curse has taken its toll on many, but my mother has been hit particularly hard. I fear her spirit and body have suffered in equal measure.
        WE_DID_EXACTLY_AS_ARCIELA_WANTED_AND_LOOK                                     = 13591,  -- We did exactly as Arciela wanted, and look where that has gotten us.
        MY_FATHER_THAT_ASSERTION_SO_ANY_STRUGGLE_OF                                   = 13592,  -- My father [continues to make/had previously made] that assertion, so any struggle of words between you was inevitable.
        HIS_STUBBORNNESS_IS_BEYOND_PARALLEL_ESPECIALLY_WHEN_PRESENTED                 = 13593,  -- His stubbornness is beyond parallel, especially when presented with evidence to the contrary.
        AND_YOU_YOUR_BLITHE_NAIVETE_IS_RATHER_INCOMPARABLE                            = 13594,  -- And you? Your blithe naivete is rather incomparable as well.
        AND_YOU_YOUR_INVECTIVE_LANGUAGE                                               = 13595,  -- And you, your invective language.
        MARCELLURIN_AND_I_GREW_UP_TOGETHER                                            = 13596,  -- Marcellurin and I grew up together.
        NOTHING_IN_LIFE_IS_EVER_EASY_LEAST_OF                                         = 13597,  -- Nothing in life is ever easy--least of all our relationship. My mother failed a purgation ritual, losing all that she held dear...and thus Hildebert took me in.
        BUT_THE_DISTANCE_BETWEEN_US_HAS_ALWAYS_BEEN                                   = 13598,  -- But the distance between us has always been great. Only Marcellurin treated me as true family.
        HE_REMAINED_BY_MY_SIDE_THROUGH_THICK_AND                                      = 13599,  -- He remained by my side through thick and thin, especially when the tragedy of my mother's passing grew too much to bear.
        WHAT_WOULD_THAT_SAY_ABOUT_ME_WERE_I                                           = 13600,  -- What would that say about me were I to stand idle while a similar fate threatens to ravage him?
        BUT_THE_BLIND_FOOL_FAILS_TO_RECOGNIZE_THAT                                    = 13601,  -- But the blind fool fails to recognize that the possibility is staring him down.
        SHOULD_THE_WORST_STRIKE_HIM_UNAWARES_I_FEAR                                   = 13602,  -- Should the worst strike him unawares, I fear it would crush him beyond repair.
        IF_ANYONE_CAN_PREDICT_HIS_REACTION_IT_IS                                      = 13603,  -- If anyone can predict his reaction, it is me. The boy is blissfully half-witted.
        COME_NOW_WOULD_SOMEONE_SENSITIVE_BE_ABLE_TO                                   = 13604,  -- Come, now. Would someone sensitive be able to withstand my acid tongue for this many years?
        CHOOSE_YOUR_RESPONSE_CAREFULLY_I_SUPPOSE_NOT_OH                               = 13605,  -- Choose your response carefully. ...I suppose not. ...Oh, I wouldn't say that...
        BAH                                                                           = 13606,  -- Bah!
        WHAT_AM_I_THINKING_GUSHING_WITH_EMOTION_TO                                    = 13607,  -- What am I thinking, gushing with emotion to the likes of you?
        THE_ONLY_ONE_IN_THIS_CITY_WHO_PAYS                                            = 13608,  -- The only one in this city who pays you a lick of attention is Arciela.
        BUT_YOU_ARE_NOT_THE_ONLY_ONE_WHO                                              = 13609,  -- But you are not the only one who supports her. I, too, must do my part to unite the city under her banner.
        I_AM_DUE_FOR_A_MEETING_WITH_GRATZIGG                                          = 13610,  -- I am due for a meeting with Gratzigg at the Peacekeepers' Coalition before sundown.
